\toc3 Yehoshua
\mt1 Yehoshua
\mt2 (Joshua)
\is1 Introduction
\ip This account about Yehoshua, traditionally вҖҳJoshuaвҖҷ in English (after вҖҳIвҖҷ and then вҖҳJвҖҷ changed over the centuries from a вҖҳYвҖҷ sound), tells how the Israelis invaded Canaan and took control of the land. Yehoshua led them forward now after replacing Mosheh (Moses) when he passed away somewhere on a mountain. Some of the main events described in this document include: their crossing the Yordan river, the demolition of Yericho (traditionally вҖҳJerichoвҖҷ), the war at Ay, the allocation of blocks of land to the various Israeli tribes and others, and the renewal of the agreement between God and his people.
\ip The most well-known saying in this account is, вҖңвҖҰchoose for yourselves today who you will serveвҖҰ But as for me and my household, we will serve Yahweh.вҖқ (24:15).
\iot Main components of this account
\io1 The defeat of the Canaanites \ior 1:1вҖ“12:24\ior*
\io1 The division of land \ior 13:1вҖ“21:45\ior*
\io2 a. The land east of the River Yordan \ior 13:1-33\ior*
\io2 b. The land west of the River Yordan \ior 14:1вҖ“19:51\ior*
\io2 c. The refuge cities \ior 20:1-9\ior*
\io2 d. The cities for Levites \ior 21:1-45\ior*
\io1 The returning home of some tribes back to the east of the Yordan \ior 22:1-34\ior*
\io1 Yehoshua's final instructions \ior 23:1-16\ior*
\io1 The renewal of the agreement there at Shikim \ior 24:1-33\ior*
\rem This is still a very early look into the unfinished text of the Open English Translation of the Bible. Please double-check the text in advance before using in public.
\ie
\c 1
\s1 Yahweh encourages Yehoshua
\rem /s1 God Commands Joshua to Conquer Canaan; God's Commission to Joshua; The Lord Commands Joshua; The Lord's Charge to Joshua; Prelude to the conquest of Canaan
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 After the deathВҰ99059 of Yahweh's servant Mosheh \add (MosesВҰ99060)\add*, Yahweh spoke to Mosheh's servant Yehoshua \add (Joshua)\add* (the son of NunВҰ99070), saying,
\v 2 вҖңNow that my servantВҰ99076 MoshehВҰ99075 is dead, youВҰ99085 and all \add #these\add* peopleВҰ99088 \add вүҲshould pack up\add* \add and\add* crossВҰ99080 over this \add River\add* YordanВҰ99083 \add to go\add* to the land that I am aboutВҰ99095 to giveВҰ99095 to themвҖ”to Yisra'el's descendants.
\v 3 I'll give youВҰ99109 all every placeВҰ99102 thatВҰ99103 the \add #soles\add* of yourВҰ99107 \add #feet\add* treadВҰ99104 on, just like I told MoshehВҰ99115.\x + \xo 1:3-5: \xt Deu 11:24-25.\x*
\v 4 Your \add вүҲterritoryВҰ99137 will extend\add* from the wildernessВҰ99117 \add in the south\add* to the LebanonВҰ99118 \add mountains in the north\add*, and from the large EuphratesВҰ99126 River \add in the east\add*, and \add вүҲright to the Mediterranean\add* seaВҰ99132 \add вүҲin the west\add*, includingВҰ99118 all of the Hittites' land.
\v 5 No man will \add вүҲbe able to challenge your leadership as long as you live\add*вҖ”I'llВҰ99152 be with you just as I was with MoshehВҰ99151вҖ”I won'tВҰ99154 fail you or abandonВҰ99157 you.\x + \xo 1:5: \xt Deu 31:6,8; Heb 13:5.\x*
\v 6 Be strongВҰ99159 and be courageousВҰ99160, for you yourself will \add вүҲlead\add* \add #these\add* peopleВҰ99166 to inheritВҰ99163 the land that I promised theirВҰ99174 ancestorsВҰ99174 that I'd giveВҰ99175 to them.\x + \xo 1:6: \xt Deu 31:6-7,23.\x*
\v 7 Just be strongВҰ99179 and very courageousВҰ99180вҖ”making sure that you \add вүҲobey everything\add* that my servantВҰ99190 MoshehВҰ99189 instructedВҰ99188 you. Don't turnВҰ99193 away to the rightВҰ99195 or to the left from it, so that you'll be wise in every \add вүҲsituation that you end up in\add*.
\v 8 ThatВҰ99225 book of the law \add ^must always be on your lips\add* and you should meditateВҰ99210 on it dayВҰ99212 and nightВҰ99213, so that you'll be careful to follow everythingВҰ99217 that's writtenВҰ99219 in it, because then you'll make your waysВҰ99227 prosperous and then you'll be wise.
\v 9 Didn't I order you to be strongВҰ99233 and courageousВҰ99234? Don't tremble or be discouraged because your godВҰ99244 YahwehВҰ99243 will be withВҰ99245 you whereverВҰ99246 you goВҰ99247.вҖқ
\s1 Yehoshua instructs the people
\rem /s1 Preparations for the Invasion; Joshua Gives Orders to the People; Joshua's Charge to the Israelites
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 10 Then Yehoshua instructedВҰ99250 the leaders of the peopleВҰ99255,
\v 11 вҖңGo right through the campВҰ99261 and tell the peopleВҰ99265: Get everything ready that you'll all need because inВҰ99260 threeВҰ99273 daysВҰ99274 we'll be ready to crossВҰ99276 over this river and enter the land that your godВҰ99288 YahwehВҰ99287 is about to giveВҰ99289 to you, and to takeВҰ99282 control of itВҰ99291.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 To the descendants of Reuben and Gad, and to the half-tribe of MenashshehВҰ99298, Yehoshua saidВҰ99299,\x + \xo 1:12-15: \xt Num 32:28-32; Deu 3:18-20; Josh 22:1-6.\x*
\v 13 вҖңRememberВҰ99303 what Yahweh's servantВҰ99311 MoshehВҰ99310 informed you: Your godВҰ99316 Yahweh is about give this land to you and to \add вүҲenable you all to settle down\add*.
\v 14 Your women and children and your livestockВҰ99328 will stay \add here\add* inВҰ99335 the land thatВҰ99331 MoshehВҰ99334 \add вүҲallocated\add* to you onВҰ99335 \add вүҲthis eastern\add* side of the YordanВҰ99336 River. ButВҰ99328 your \add soldiers\add* mustВҰ99329 dress for battleВҰ99339 and crossВҰ99338 over ahead of your brothersВҰ99341 and helpВҰ99345 them
\v 15 until Yahweh enables your brothersВҰ99354 to \add вүҲtake over the land thatВҰ99363 your godВҰ99366 Yahweh is aboutВҰ99367 to give them so they can settle like you all have\add*. Then you'll all be able to returnВҰ99369 to this land which Yahweh's servantВҰ99379 MoshehВҰ99378 gaveВҰ99376 you onВҰ99381 \add вүҲthis eastern side of the YordanВҰ99382 and take full control of it\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңWe'llВҰ99389 do everythingВҰ99398 you'veВҰ99394 toldВҰ99394 us to,вҖқ the people answeredВҰ99386, вҖңandВҰ99396 we'll goВҰ99402 whereverВҰ99400 you sendВҰ99401 us.
\v 17 We'll listenВҰ99412 to you just like we listenedВҰ99407 to everythingВҰ99404 Mosheh said. May your godВҰ99417 YahwehВҰ99416 be with you, just like he was with Mosheh.
\v 18 We'll put anyone to deathВҰ99444 who rebelsВҰ99430 againstВҰ99430 your wordsВҰ99439 or refuses to follow your instructions. Just stay strongВҰ99446 and courageousВҰ99447.вҖқ
\c 2
\s1 Spies sent to Yericho
\rem /s1 In central Canaan; Rahab Protects the Spies; Rahab and the Spies; Spies Sent to Jericho; Joshua Sends Spies into Jericho
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Then from \add there at\add* \add вүҲAcacia Grove\add*, Yehoshua (Nun'sВҰ99455 son) secretlyВҰ99463 sentВҰ99450 off twoВҰ99459 spiesВҰ99462, saying, вҖңGo \add вүҲand learn about the land over there, especially around\add* YerichoВҰ99472 \add City\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* they wentВҰ99473 off, and \add over there,\add* they entered the houseВҰ99475 of a womanВҰ99477вҖ”a prostituteВҰ99478 named RahabВҰ99480вҖ”and they lay down there.\x + \xo 2:1: \xt Heb 11:31; Jam 2:25.\x*
\v 2 \add вүҲHowever, someone told\add* Yericho'sВҰ99487 kingВҰ99486, вҖңListen, some IsraeliВҰ99495 menВҰ99490 arrived here tonight to \add вүҲcheck out our\add* land.вҖқ
\v 3 SoВҰ99501 the kingВҰ99502 sentВҰ99501 \add guards\add* to tell RahabВҰ99506, вҖңBringВҰ99503 out the menВҰ99509 who \add вүҲwentВҰ99510 to yourВҰ99515 place\add* andВҰ99501 \add вүҲstayed the night\add*, because they've comeВҰ99523 here to \add вүҲcheck out\add* our land!вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲHowever, Rahab had hiddenВҰ99531\add* the two men \add вүҲso she answered\add*, вҖңIndeed, the men \add вүҲarrived here, butВҰ99525\add* I didn'tВҰ99538 know whereВҰ99540 they were from.
\v 5 \add вүҲButВҰ99543 as\add* the \add city\add* gateВҰ99544 was \add вүҲaboutВҰ99545\add* to shut \add вүҲlast night\add*, the men went out. IВҰ99550 don'tВҰ99549 know to whereВҰ99551 \add *they\add* wentвҖ”if you all hurry, you might be able to \add вүҲcatch\add* them.вҖқ
\v 6 (\add вүҲButВҰ99560 actually\add* she had takenВҰ99561 them up onto her \add flat\add* roof andВҰ99560 hiddenВҰ99563 them inВҰ99564 \add вүҲbundles of flax thatВҰ99566 were drying there\add*.)
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ99576\add* the \add вүҲguards hurried\add* out on the roadВҰ99575 to the fordsВҰ99578 on the YordanВҰ99576 \add River\add* andВҰ99579 the \add city\add* gateВҰ99579 was kept shut after \add *they\add* had left.
\p
\v 8 Before the Israeli men lay down \add to sleep that night\add*, \add @Rahab\add* wentВҰ99591 up them on the roofВҰ99595
\v 9 and told \add *them\add*, вҖң\add #We\add* knowВҰ99601 that YahwehВҰ99605 has givenВҰ99604 this land to you all and we're \add вүҲall terrified\add* of you. EveryoneВҰ99601 that lives here is \add вүҲtrembling at the thought of yourВҰ99613 coming\add*
\v 10 because we've heard thatВҰ99639 YahwehВҰ99629 driedВҰ99628 up the waterВҰ99632 of the Red Sea ahead of you all when you leftВҰ99637 EgyptВҰ99638 \add (MitsrayimВҰ99638)\add*. And \add вүЎwe heard\add* what you all did to two of the AmoriteВҰ99643 kingsВҰ99642 SihonВҰ99647 and OgВҰ99648 over the YordanВҰ99646 thereвҖ”how you all completely destroyedВҰ99650 them.\x + \xo 2:10: a \xt Exo 14:21; \xo b \xt Num 21:21-35.\x*
\v 11 \add вүҲYes,\add* we've heardВҰ99653 \add <the reports\add* and \add вүҲwe trembled and lost ourВҰ99655 courage to fight youВҰ99662 all\add* becauseВҰ99662 yourВҰ99665 god YahwehВҰ99664, he's GodВҰ99665 \add вүҲover\add* the heavensВҰ99668 aboveВҰ99669 and the earthВҰ99672 belowВҰ99673.
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ99675\add* now, pleaseВҰ99678 promise me by YahwehВҰ99680 that because I'veВҰ99683 been kind to \add both of\add* you, you all will act kindly towards my father'sВҰ99693 householdВҰ99692. Give me \add вүҲa guarantee that you'll do what you promise\add*
\v 13 and spareВҰ99700 my parents and my siblings and their families from deathВҰ99723.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңOur lives \add вүҲfor your lives\add*,вҖқ the \add two\add* menВҰ99727 agreed. вҖңIf you don'tВҰ99732 tell \add вүҲanyone about our agreement\add*, thenВҰ99725 when YahwehВҰ99741 givesВҰ99739 us this land, we'll \add вүҲshow\add* kindness andВҰ99725 faithfulnessВҰ99749 to you.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ99751 she put a ropeВҰ99752 out throughВҰ99753 the windowВҰ99754 to let them down \add to escape from the cityВҰ99758\add*, because herВҰ99756 houseВҰ99756 where she lived was \add actually built into\add* the side of the wall.
\v 16 вҖңGo to the hill countryВҰ99765,вҖқ she told them, вҖң\add вүҲso those searching for you won't find\add* you, andВҰ99763 hideВҰ99772 \add up\add* thereВҰ99773 for threeВҰ99774 daysВҰ99775. \add ThenВҰ99763 once\add* the searchers have returned, you'll be able to \add safely\add* \add вүҲreturn to your camp\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖң\add вүҲThis promise thatВҰ99790 you made us make\add*,вҖқ the menВҰ99785 told her, вҖң\add вүҲwon't apply unless you do this\add*:
\v 18 \add Take\add* this red cord \add and\add* when weВҰ99794 \add вүҲinvade\add* the land, tie \add *it\add* in this windowВҰ99804 \add вүҲin the wall\add*. Make sure thatВҰ99805 your parents and your siblings and their households are all here in your houseВҰ99824.
\v 19 If any of them leaves the house, \add вүҲtheir life will thenВҰ99826 be in their own hands\add* andВҰ99826 we'll be innocent \add if they're killed\add*. ButВҰ99826 if anyone withВҰ99836 you in this house \add вүҲgets injured\add*, \add вүҲwe'll be responsible for that\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲAlsoВҰ99856,\add* if you tell anyone else about this agreement, thenВҰ99853 we'll be \add вүҲreleased\add* from this promise thatВҰ99863 you made us make.вҖқ
\v 21 вҖң\add вүҲSureВҰ99874, let it be as you say\add*,вҖқ \add @Rahab\add* \add вүҲrespondedВҰ99866\add*. ThenВҰ99866 she sentВҰ99871 them off, andВҰ99866 after they'd gone, she tied the red cord inВҰ99878 her windowВҰ99878.
\p
\v 22 \add @The two men\add* wentВҰ99881 up into the hills and stayed thereВҰ99884 for threeВҰ99885 daysВҰ99886 untilВҰ99887 the search party returnedВҰ99889 \add to the city\add* after searching all the roads and not finding them.
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ99899\add* the twoВҰ99900 menВҰ99901 wentВҰ99902 down to the river and crossedВҰ99904 over and returnedВҰ99899 to YehoshuaВҰ99908 (Nun'sВҰ99911 son), and theyВҰ99905 told him everything thatВҰ99918 had happenedВҰ99918.
\v 24 вҖңYahwehВҰ99928 has certainly givenВҰ99927 this land to us,вҖқ they told Yehoshua. вҖңThe people there won't be able to resist us becauseВҰ99942 they're so terrified.вҖқ
\c 3
\s1 The Israelis cross the Yordan
\rem /s1 Israel Crosses the Jordan; The Israelites Cross the Jordan; The People of Israel Cross the Jordan; Crossing the Jordan
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Early the next morningВҰ99947, Yehoshua \add and the peopleВҰ99957\add* got up earlyВҰ99945 and set off from Acacia Grove and wentВҰ99950 as far as the YordanВҰ99953 \add River\add* and campedВҰ99959 thereВҰ99960 without crossing over.
\v 2 After threeВҰ99966 daysВҰ99967, the leaders wentВҰ99968 throughout the campВҰ99971
\v 3 and instructedВҰ99973 the peopleВҰ99976, вҖңAs soon as you all see the boxВҰ99980 \add containing\add* the agreement with your godВҰ99984 YahwehВҰ99983, and \add вүЎsee\add* the LeviticalВҰ99986 priestsВҰ99985 carryingВҰ99987 it, thenВҰ99973 you yourselves should move out from your placesВҰ99991 and follow afterВҰ99993 it.
\v 4 ButВҰ100000 keep aboutВҰ100002 nine hundred metres back from it. Don't go any closer than that so that you all can see the way to go, because \add вүҲwe haven't been this way\add* before.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 Then Yehoshua told the peopleВҰ100032, вҖң\add вүҲMake sure youВҰ100038 all do the ritual washing to make yourselvesВҰ100033 pure\add*, because tomorrowВҰ100035 YahwehВҰ100037 will do miracles among us.вҖқ
\v 6 And \add *he\add* told the priestsВҰ100045, вҖңLift up the boxВҰ100050 with the agreement, and \add вүҲwalk across here in front\add* of the people.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ100041\add* they liftedВҰ100055 up the \add sacred\add* chestВҰ100050 and went \add вүҲand stood in front of all\add* the people.
\p
\v 7 Then YahwehВҰ100066 told Yehoshua, вҖңToday I'llВҰ100072 beginВҰ100072 to make you powerful in the eyesВҰ100074 of all YisraelВҰ100077 \add (IsraelВҰ100077)\add* so they'll knowВҰ100079 that I'm with you just like I was with MoshehВҰ100085.
\v 8 Tell the priestsВҰ100093 who are carryingВҰ100094 the \add sacred\add* chestВҰ100095 that as soon as they comeВҰ100099 to the edge of the river, they should \add вүҲgo inВҰ100105 just a little andВҰ100089 thenВҰ100089 stop there\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Then Yehoshua told the IsraelisВҰ100114, вҖң\add вүҲGather around\add* here and listenВҰ100117 to yourВҰ100122 godВҰ100122 Yahweh'sВҰ100121 messageВҰ100120.вҖқ
\v 10 \add *He\add* told \add <them\add*, вҖңThis is how you'll all knowВҰ100127 that GodВҰ100129, who can do anything, is among you. With yourВҰ100131 own eyes, you'll all see how he'll take away the land from the CanaanitesВҰ100137, the HittitesВҰ100140, the HivitesВҰ100143, the PerizzitesВҰ100146, the GirgashitesВҰ100149, the AmoritesВҰ100150, andВҰ100124 the Yebusites.
\v 11 Listen, the sacred chestВҰ100154 containing the slabs that belongs to the masterВҰ100156 who \add owns\add* the whole world, is aboutВҰ100160 to \add be taken\add* across the YordanВҰ100162 inВҰ100162 front of youВҰ100161.
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ100171\add* now, \add вүҲselect one man from each of your twelve tribesВҰ100170\add*,
\v 13 andВҰ100180 as soon as the \add вүҲpriestsВҰ100184 carryingВҰ100185 the sacred chestВҰ100186 go into the YordanВҰ100193, as soon as their feetВҰ100183 touch the water, the river water onВҰ100192 the upstream side\add* will pile up inВҰ100192 a heap.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \add вүҲSoВҰ100204 once the people had packed up theirВҰ100207 tentsВҰ100207 ready to crossВҰ100208 the river\add*, the priestsВҰ100212 carryingВҰ100213 the sacred boxВҰ100214 walked ahead inВҰ100205 frontВҰ100216 of them.
\v 15 ThenВҰ100219 as soon as \add вүҲthoseВҰ100220 priestsВҰ100226\add* steeped into the \add edge\add* of the \add вүҲfast-flowing\add* river (because itВҰ100233 overflowed itsВҰ100238 banksВҰ100238 atВҰ100230 harvestВҰ100241 timeВҰ100240 \add inВҰ100230 the spring\add*),
\v 16 thenВҰ100243 the water coming from upstream \add suddenly\add* stopped flowing. The water far upstream piled up near a townВҰ100255 called AdamВҰ100253 (near Tsaretan), andВҰ100243 the water thatВҰ100256 normally flowed down towards the Sea of ArabahВҰ100262 (\add also called\add* the Dead Sea or the Salt Sea) \add вүҲstopped flowing\add*, so the peopleВҰ100268 were able to cross \add what was\add* the Yordan River opposite YerichoВҰ100271.
\v 17 The priestsВҰ100274 carryingВҰ100275 the sacred chestВҰ100276 withВҰ100280 Yahweh'sВҰ100279 agreement \add in it\add*, stoodВҰ100273 on firm, dry ground in \add what had been\add* the middleВҰ100281 of the river. All the Israelis crossedВҰ100296 over on dry ground untilВҰ100289 everyone was across.
\c 4
\s1 The memorial of boulders
\rem /s1 Twelve Stones Set Up at Gilgal; Memorial Stones Are Set Up; Memorials to the Jordan Crossing
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Once all the people had crossedВҰ100308 over the YordanВҰ100311 River, YahwehВҰ100314 told Yehoshua,
\v 2 вҖңTake \add those\add* twelve menВҰ100327 \add вүҲthat the peopleВҰ100324 selected from each tribeВҰ100334\add*,
\v 3 and give them these instructions: Pick up twelve bouldersВҰ100352 from here in the middleВҰ100343 of the YordanВҰ100344 from near where the priestsВҰ100347 are standingВҰ100345, and bring them over withВҰ100358 you, and put them in the placeВҰ100358 where you all camp tonight.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSo\add* Yehoshua calledВҰ100366 \add over\add* the twelve men, one from each tribeВҰ100383,
\v 5 and told them, вҖңCross \add вүҲback to where\add* your godВҰ100392 Yahweh'sВҰ100391 boxВҰ100390 is in the middleВҰ100395 of the YordanВҰ100396 and \add вүҲeach of youВҰ100398 should pick up a rockВҰ100400 and carry it back on your\add* shoulderвҖ”one stoneВҰ100400 each on your shoulder to match the numberВҰ100405 of tribesВҰ100406 of Yisra'el's sons.
\v 6 \add вүҲThose boulders will be a monument for all the people\add*. \add вүҲIn the future when yourВҰ100419 childrenВҰ100419 askВҰ100418 what those boulders mean\add*,
\v 7 thenВҰ100427 you'll all be able to tell them that the water in the YordanВҰ100432 River was cut off ahead of the boxВҰ100434 withВҰ100438 Yahweh'sВҰ100437 agreement. WhenВҰ100427 itВҰ100438 crossedВҰ100438 over into the river, the water in the river \add вүҲstopped flowing\add*, andВҰ100443 those bouldersВҰ100444 are a memorialВҰ100446 for the IsraelisВҰ100448 forever.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ100453\add* the IsraelisВҰ100458 did just what Yehoshua had toldВҰ100461 them to do, and they picked up twelve bouldersВҰ100467 from the YordanВҰ100469, just as YahwehВҰ100472 had instructedВҰ100461 Yehoshua, and brought them over to where \add the people\add* were camping and placedВҰ100485 them down thereВҰ100487.
\v 9 ThenВҰ100489 YehoshuaВҰ100493 stacked up twelve other bouldersВҰ100491 in the middleВҰ100494 of the YordanВҰ100495 where the feetВҰ100498 of the priestsВҰ100499 carryingВҰ100500 the boxВҰ100501 with the agreement had been, andВҰ100503 theyВҰ100503 remain thereВҰ100504 untilВҰ100505 today.
\v 10 The priestsВҰ100509 carryingВҰ100510 the boxВҰ100511 had stood in the middleВҰ100513 of the YordanВҰ100514 untilВҰ100515 everythingВҰ100517 thatВҰ100520 YahwehВҰ100523 had instructed Yehoshua to pass on to the people was done, just as MoshehВҰ100535 had \add also\add* instructed Yehoshua, andВҰ100509 the people had rapidly crossedВҰ100541 over.
\p
\v 11 As soon as all the people had crossed over, the priestsВҰ100555 carrying Yahweh'sВҰ100554 boxВҰ100552 \add also\add* crossed over in frontВҰ100556 of the people.
\v 12 TheВҰ100572 \add soldiers\add* from the tribesВҰ100567 of ReubenВҰ100562, and GadВҰ100565 and the half-tribe of MenashshehВҰ100568 had \add вүҲmarched\add* over ahead of the rest of the IsraeliВҰ100571, as MoshehВҰ100576 had \add вүҲagreed with them\add*.
\v 13 (\add ThereВҰ100584 were\add* around fortyВҰ100578 thousandВҰ100579 of them, armed and ready for battle, and theyВҰ100582 were heading to the plainsВҰ100587 of YerichoВҰ100588 for the battle \add there\add*.)
\v 14 On that dayВҰ100591, YahwehВҰ100594 helped Yehoshua to look powerful in the eyesВҰ100598 of the people, and they respected him just as they had respected Mosheh all the daysВҰ100611 of his\f + \fr 4:14 \ft The Hebrew doesn't make it clear here whether the writer meant all of \+bd Mosheh's life\+bd* or all of \+bd Yehoshua's life\+bd*, so translations will vary.\f* life.
\p
\v 15 Then YahwehВҰ100616 told Yehoshua,
\v 16 вҖң\add вүҲNow order\add* the priestsВҰ100625 carryingВҰ100626 the boxВҰ100627 with the agreement to comeВҰ100629 up out of \add what was\add* the YordanВҰ100632 \add River\add*,вҖқ
\v 17 so YehoshuaВҰ100635 instructedВҰ100634 the priestsВҰ100638 to comeВҰ100640 on up from the YordanВҰ100643.
\v 18 As soon as the priestsВҰ100648 carryingВҰ100649 the boxВҰ100650 withВҰ100646 Yahweh'sВҰ100653 agreement cameВҰ100646 up out of \add what had been\add* the YordanВҰ100655 \add River\add* and theirВҰ100666 feetВҰ100658 stepped onto \add what had been\add* dry land, the river waterВҰ100663 returnedВҰ100662 to its placeВҰ100666 and overflowed it banksВҰ100675 as \add вүҲit had been doing for the previous few daysВҰ100670\add*.
\p
\v 19 The peopleВҰ100677 had come up from the river valley \add вүҲaround the end of March\add* andВҰ100685 theyВҰ100678 campedВҰ100685 east of YerichoВҰ100689 atВҰ100682 GilgalВҰ100686,
\v 20 whichВҰ100696 was where \add #they\add* had set up the \add monument of\add* twelve bouldersВҰ100694.
\v 21 ThenВҰ100705 \add @Yehoshua\add* told the IsraelisВҰ100709, вҖң\add вүҲInВҰ100715 the future\add* when yourВҰ100713 descendants askВҰ100712 why theseВҰ100721 bouldersВҰ100720 are here,
\v 22 tell them that this is where YisraelВҰ100730 crossed the YordanВҰ100733 \add River\add* onВҰ100728 dry land.
\v 23 YourВҰ100745 godВҰ100740 YahwehВҰ100739 dried up the river waterВҰ100743 ahead of you until you'd all crossed over, just as \add *he\add* had done when he dried up the Red Sea before we crossed over.
\v 24 YahwehВҰ100773 did that so that all the peoplesВҰ100768 in the world would knowВҰ100765 that he is powerful, \add and\add* so that you'll always all respect him.
\c 5
\rem /s1 The New Generation Circumcised; Circumcision at Gilgal
\p
\v 1 When all the AmoriteВҰ100793 kings who were onВҰ100795 the \add west\add* side of the Yordan (towards the ocean) and all the CanaaniteВҰ100801 kings (beside the ocean) heardВҰ100789 how YahwehВҰ100810 had driedВҰ100809 up the waterВҰ100813 inВҰ100795 the Yordan \add River\add* untilВҰ100819 \add @the IsraelisВҰ100818\add* had crossedВҰ100821 over, they \add вүҲtrembled withВҰ100795 fear\add* and \add вүҲlost theirВҰ100824 nerve to stand against\add* YisraelВҰ100818.
\s1 Circumcising the males and celebrating вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ at Gilgal
\rem /s1 The Circumcision at Gilgal; Israel Reestablishes Covenant Ceremonies
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 2 At that timeВҰ100837, YahwehВҰ100840 told Yehoshua, вҖңMake yourselfВҰ100845 flintВҰ100847 knivesВҰ100846 andВҰ100848 againВҰ100848 circumciseВҰ100849 the male IsraelisВҰ100854.вҖқ
\v 3 SoВҰ100857 Yehoshua \add had\add* flintВҰ100862 knivesВҰ100861 made andВҰ100863 the \add male\add* IsraelisВҰ100867 were circumcisedВҰ100863 at \add a place they named\add* вҖҳThe hill of foreskinsВҰ100871вҖҷ.
\v 4 (This was done because all the menВҰ100887 who'd leftВҰ100882 EgyptВҰ100883 andВҰ100873 who were old enough to join the army \add had been circumcisedВҰ100877 butВҰ100873\add* had diedВҰ100889 inВҰ100890 the wildernessВҰ100890 since thenВҰ100873,\x + \xo 5:6: \xt Num 14:28-35.\x*
\v 5 \add and\add* because all the \add вүҲboys\add* who'd been born while they were inВҰ100907 the wildernessВҰ100907 after they'd leftВҰ100902 EgyptВҰ100910 hadn't been circumcised.
\v 6 The IsraelisВҰ100922 had spent fortyВҰ100917 years \add вүҲmoving\add* around the wildernessВҰ100923 untilВҰ100924 the last of those menВҰ100930 who'd leftВҰ100932 EgyptВҰ100933 butВҰ100958 hadn't listenedВҰ100937 to Yahweh \add вүҲhad died\add*. Yahweh had promised not to let them seeВҰ100945 the land thatВҰ100949 \add *he'd\add* promised to theirВҰ100952 ancestorsВҰ100952 to giveВҰ100953 themвҖ”a land flowingВҰ100956 withВҰ100923 milk and honeyВҰ100958.
\v 7 It was the sons of those peopleВҰ100975 that Yehoshua had circumcised \add this time\add* because theyВҰ100971 hadn't been circumcised onВҰ100977 the wayВҰ100977.)
\p
\v 8 After all theirВҰ100988 males had been circumcisedВҰ100986, they remained inВҰ100989 that campВҰ100989 untilВҰ100990 they'd \add вүҲhealedВҰ100991 up\add*.
\v 9 Then YahwehВҰ100995 told Yehoshua, вҖңToday I'veВҰ101000 rolledВҰ101000 away the disgrace of EgyptВҰ101004 from you,вҖқ and that placeВҰ101008 is named Gilgal\f + \fr 5:9 \ft The name вҖҳGilgalвҖҷ (вҖҳЧ’ЦјЦҙЧңЦ°Ч’ЦјЦёЧңвҖҷ, вҖҳcircleвҖҷ) sounds like вҖҳgalalвҖҷ (вҖҳЧ’ЦјЦ·ЧңЦ·ЧңвҖҷ, вҖҳrollвҖҷ).\f* untilВҰ101011 this day.
\rem /s1 The Passover at Gilgal
\p
\v 10 InВҰ101018 the eveningВҰ101028 of \add вүҲthe fourth dayВҰ101026 that the peopleВҰ101016 had been campedВҰ101015\add* atВҰ101019 GilgalВҰ101019 there onВҰ101019 the plainsВҰ101029 near YerichoВҰ101030, theyВҰ101020 celebrated the вҖҳpass-overвҖҷ.\x + \xo 5:10: \xt Exo 12:1-13.\x*
\s1 Eating from the landвҖ”no more manna
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 11 The next day they ate roastedВҰ101038 grainВҰ101038 that \add they'd taken from that area\add*, andВҰ101032 ate flat breadВҰ101037 that same day.
\v 12 TheВҰ101054 dayВҰ101045 afterВҰ101045 they'd eaten some of the produce from that area, there was no manna \add onВҰ101046 the ground to be collected\add* andВҰ101043 \add so\add* it stoppedвҖ”instead they'd eat the produce from the CanaanВҰ101059 regionВҰ101058 \add beginning\add* that yearВҰ101060.\x + \xo 5:12: \xt Exo 16:35.\x*
\s1 Yehoshua and the man with a sword
\rem /s1 The Lord's Commander Confronts Joshua; Joshua and the Man with a Sword; The Fall of Jericho; Joshua's Vision
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 13 While Yehoshua was in the YerichoВҰ101067 \add area\add*, he looked up and saw a man in frontВҰ101075 of him. The man had drawnВҰ101077 his swordВҰ101076 and was holding it in his handВҰ101078 \add вүҲso\add* Yehoshua approached him and asked, вҖңAre you onВҰ101065 \em our\em* side, or withВҰ101065 our enemies?вҖқ
\p
\v 14 вҖңNo,вҖқ the man \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңbutВҰ101090 I, the leader of Yahweh'sВҰ101099 army, have comeВҰ101101 now.вҖқ
\p ThenВҰ101090 Yehoshua fell \add вүҲto his knees\add* and bowedВҰ101108 down with his face to the ground, and \add вүҲasked\add* him, вҖңWhat's my masterВҰ101112 going to \add вүҲcommandВҰ101095\add* to his servantВҰ101116?вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңTake off your sandalsВҰ101128,вҖқ the commanderВҰ101119 of Yahweh'sВҰ101122 army told \add *him\add*, вҖңbecause the ground thatВҰ101133 you'reВҰ101134 standingВҰ101135 is holy.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ101118\add* Yehoshua \add вүҲtook them off\add*.
\c 6
\s1 Yericho's walls collapse
\rem /s1 Jericho Taken and Destroyed; The Fall of Jericho
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow\add* YerichoВҰ101143 \add city\add* was shut-up tightly \add вүҲbecause of the IsraelisВҰ101148\add*, \add so\add* no one was comingВҰ101152 out andВҰ101143 no one could go in.
\v 2 Then YahwehВҰ101156 told Yehoshua, вҖңListen, I'veВҰ101161 givenВҰ101161 you \add вүҲvictory over\add* YerichoВҰ101165 and itsВҰ101168 kingВҰ101168, and \add вүҲtheir\add* mightyВҰ101169 army \add >warriors\add*.
\v 3 All your soldiers mustВҰ101172 go aroundВҰ101172 the city once every day for six days
\v 4 withВҰ101198 seven priests \add вүҲblowing\add* ram's horns going ahead of the sacred boxВҰ101197. OnВҰ101201 the seventh dayВҰ101198, you all mustВҰ101192 go around the cityВҰ101203 seven timesВҰ101205 while the priests are blowing the horns.
\v 5 \add вүҲFinallyВҰ101217,\add* withВҰ101211 a long blastВҰ101211 of the horn, when you all hear that thenВҰ101210 all the people mustВҰ101221 shout loudlyВҰ101226 and the wall aroundВҰ101230 the cityВҰ101229 will fall down flat, and all the \add вүҲsoldiers\add* should go straightВҰ101234 inВҰ101211 \add from where they're standing\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ101236\add* Yehoshua summoned the priests and told them, вҖңCarry the box with the agreement, and have seven priests hold up seven rams' hornsВҰ101256 \add вүҲahead\add* of Yahweh'sВҰ101259 box.вҖқ
\v 7 ThenВҰ101261 he told the peopleВҰ101265, вҖңGoВҰ101268 across in frontВҰ101273 andВҰ101261 goВҰ101267 aroundВҰ101267 the cityВҰ101270, \add вүҲwith the soldiers going ahead\add* of Yahweh'sВҰ101275 boxВҰ101274.вҖқ
\p
\v 8 After Yehoshua had spokenВҰ101278 to the peopleВҰ101282, the seven priestsВҰ101284 with their seven rams' horns went across inВҰ101293 frontВҰ101289 and blew the horns, and the boxВҰ101294 with Yahweh's covenantВҰ101295 was \add вүҲcarried\add* along behindВҰ101298 them.
\v 9 The \add вүҲsoldiers\add* walked ahead of the priestsВҰ101303 blowing the horns, withВҰ101313 the rear guardВҰ101307 walking behindВҰ101309 the boxВҰ101310. \add SoВҰ101300\add* they were walking andВҰ101300 blowing the horns,
\v 10 andВҰ101315 Yehoshua toldВҰ101318 the peopleВҰ101317, вҖңDon't shout \add вүҲor even speak or make a noise\add* untilВҰ101334 the dayВҰ101335 I tell you all to shoutвҖ”thenВҰ101315 you all should shout loudly.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ101341\add* Yahweh'sВҰ101344 boxВҰ101342 was carried once aroundВҰ101341 the cityВҰ101347, thenВҰ101341 the people wentВҰ101341 back to the camp andВҰ101341 stayedВҰ101353 the nightВҰ101353 there.
\p
\v 12 YehoshuaВҰ101358 got up earlyВҰ101357 the next morningВҰ101359, and the priestsВҰ101361 picked up Yahweh'sВҰ101365 boxВҰ101364
\v 13 and the seven priestsВҰ101368 holding the seven rams' horns went in front of \add *it\add*вҖ”blowingВҰ101378 the horns as they kept walking. The \add вүҲsoldiers\add* walking in front of them, and the rear guardВҰ101383 walked behindВҰ101385 Yahweh's boxВҰ101374 \add вүҲwhile\add* the horns were being blown.
\v 14 TheyВҰ101394 wentВҰ101393 once aroundВҰ101393 the cityВҰ101396 on that secondВҰ101398 dayВҰ101397 andВҰ101401 thenВҰ101393 returnedВҰ101401 to their campВҰ101402 \add again\add*вҖ”doing that for sixВҰ101405 daysВҰ101406.
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ101408 on the seventh day they got up earlyВҰ101412 at dawn andВҰ101408 went around the city \add вүҲas before\add*, except this day they went around seven times.
\v 16 \add вүҲAfter that seventhВҰ101435 timeВҰ101434 around,\add* the priestsВҰ101437 blew \add a long blastВҰ101436\add* onВҰ101434 the rams' horns andВҰ101439 Yehoshua told the peopleВҰ101443, вҖңShout, because YahwehВҰ101448 has givenВҰ101447 youВҰ101449 all the cityВҰ101452!
\v 17 \add However,\add* everything in the cityВҰ101455 is sacred to YahwehВҰ101463. Only the prostituteВҰ101466 RahabВҰ101465 andВҰ101454 those who are in her houseВҰ101473 will be allowed to liveВҰ101467, because she hid the spies that we sentВҰ101480 in.
\v 18 ButВҰ101482 for all of you, everything inside the city is forbiddenвҖ”if any of you takeВҰ101492 anything out of the city then our campВҰ101499 \add вүҲwould also then be marked for destructionВҰ101491\add* andВҰ101482 itВҰ101503 would cause \add a lot of\add* troubleВҰ101502.
\v 19 AllВҰ101514 the silverВҰ101507 and goldВҰ101508, bronzeВҰ101510 and iron is dedicated to YahwehВҰ101516 and mustВҰ101517 goВҰ101517 into \add *his\add* treasuryВҰ101515.
\p
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ101519\add* the people shoutedВҰ101532 when that horn blewвҖ”as soon as they heardВҰ101524 \add *it\add* the people shouted loudlyВҰ101533 and the wall fell down onВҰ101522 itself and the people went up \add and over\add* into the city from wherever they were standing and capturedВҰ101542 the city.\x + \xo 6:20: \xt Heb 11:30.\x*
\v 21 TheyВҰ101548 \add вүҲkilled\add* every \add living thing\add* inВҰ101553 the cityВҰ101553 withВҰ101553 their \add #swords\add*, includingВҰ101555 men and women, youngВҰ101558 and old, even cattle, sheepВҰ101564, and donkeysВҰ101565.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ101570 Yehoshua commanded the two menВҰ101571 who had spiedВҰ101572 on the area, вҖңGo to the prostitute'sВҰ101582 houseВҰ101579 and bringВҰ101583 the woman out of it and all who are related to her, just as you promised her.вҖқ
\v 23 \add вүҲSoВҰ101599\add* the youngВҰ101600 menВҰ101600 \add вүҲwho'd gone in as\add* spiesВҰ101601 wentВҰ101599 in and brought out RahabВҰ101605 and her parents and all her relatives and settled them outsideВҰ101628 of the campВҰ101629 of the IsraelisВҰ101630.
\v 24 ThenВҰ101632 \add @the warriors\add* set fireВҰ101634 to the cityВҰ101632 and burntВҰ101633 everything that was inВҰ101634 itВҰ101639. Only the silverВҰ101642 and goldВҰ101643, and bronzeВҰ101645 and iron were \add first removed and\add* put into the treasuryВҰ101648 of Yahweh'sВҰ101651 houseВҰ101649.
\v 25 \add вүҲButВҰ101653\add* Yehoshua spared the prostituteВҰ101656 RahabВҰ101655 and her father'sВҰ101660 householdВҰ101659 and her other relatives because she hid the men that Yehoshua had sentВҰ101683 in to spy onВҰ101671 YerichoВҰ101688, and she still lives in YisraelВҰ101672 to this dayВҰ101674.\x + \xo 6:25: \xt Heb 11:31.\x*
\p
\v 26 At that time, Yehoshua made \add @the people\add* take an oath, saying,\x + \xo 6:26: \xt 1Ki 16:34.\x*
\q1 вҖңMay YahwehВҰ101699 curseВҰ101696 anyone who rebuildsВҰ101702 this city, YerichoВҰ101709.
\q1 When that person lays its foundationВҰ101711, may his oldest son die.
\q1 And when he finishes buildingВҰ101702 the city wall and sets up its gatesВҰ101714, may his youngestВҰ101712 son die.вҖқ
\p
\v 27 \add вүҲSoВҰ101716\add* YahwehВҰ101717 was with YehoshuaВҰ101720 andВҰ101716 \add вүҲeveryone in that region had heard about himВҰ101722\add*.
\c 7
\s1 Achan's sin
\rem /s1 Ai Defeats the Israelites; The Sin of Achan and Its Punishment; Achan's Sin
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲHowever\add* the Israelis disobeyed the command about \add вүҲnot taking anything\add*. AchanВҰ101734 (son of Karmi, son of ZabdiВҰ101740, son of ZerahВҰ101743, from the tribeВҰ101744 of YehudahВҰ101745) tookВҰ101733 something that was prohibited, \add вүҲso\add* YahwehВҰ101752 was angry withВҰ101732 the Israelis.
\p
\v 2 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* Yehoshua sent some of his men from YerichoВҰ101759 to Ay (east of Beyt-El and near Beyt-Aven) and told them, вҖңGo \add вүҲto Ay\add* and spy out the land.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ101756\add* the men went and checkout out Ay.
\v 3 \add вүҲWhenВҰ101785\add* they returnedВҰ101785 to Yehoshua, they told him, вҖңDon't \add вүҲsend all the warriors\add*вҖ”\add only\add* around two to threeВҰ101800 thousandВҰ101797 men shouldВҰ101793 go andВҰ101785 attackВҰ101804 them. Don't \add вүҲbother everyoneВҰ101796 else\add* because \add вүҲAy is small\add*.вҖқ
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ101822\add* around threeВҰ101827 thousandВҰ101828 \add вүҲwarriorsВҰ101832\add* wentВҰ101822 to \add attack AyВҰ101833, butВҰ101822 they were defeated\add* andВҰ101830 had to flee \add back\add*.
\v 5 The menВҰ101837 from Ay chasedВҰ101842 them from the city gateВҰ101844 downhill to Shevarim and fought them onВҰ101849 the slopes. About thirty-sixВҰ101839 \add вүҲof them\add* were killedВҰ101835, and the \add вүҲIsraelis became very afraid and lost all their courage\add*.
\p
\v 6 Yehoshua and the IsraeliВҰ101872 eldersВҰ101872 tore their clothesВҰ101859 \add in grief\add* and fell to their knees in frontВҰ101865 of Yahweh'sВҰ101867 boxВҰ101866 untilВҰ101868 eveningВҰ101870, throwing dust onto their headsВҰ101878 \add in despair\add*.
\v 7 ThenВҰ101880 Yehoshua \add вүҲasked\add*, вҖңYahwehВҰ101885, my masterВҰ101884, why did youВҰ101887 bring \add #these\add* peopleВҰ101891 across the YordanВҰ101905 and thenВҰ101880 let us be defeated and killed by the AmoritesВҰ101899? If only we'd been content and stayed onВҰ101898 the otherВҰ101904 side of the river.
\v 8 Please, my masterВҰ101908, what can I sayВҰ101910 now that \add *we\add* have had to flee \add in shame\add* from our enemiesВҰ101917?
\v 9 \add WhenВҰ101927\add* the CanaanitesВҰ101920 and the other people living in this land hearВҰ101919 \add <about this\add*, they'll surroundВҰ101924 us and \add вүҲkill all of us\add*. ThenВҰ101919 what would youВҰ101935 do to defend yourВҰ101936 honour?
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ101940\add* YahwehВҰ101941 told Yehoshua, вҖңStand up! Why is yourВҰ101953 faceВҰ101953 \add вүҲon the ground like that\add*?
\v 11 YisraelВҰ101956 has sinnedВҰ101955 and disobeyed my agreement\f + \fr 7:11 \ft Probably referring to the ten commands written on the stone slabs.\f* thatВҰ101962 I made with them. They've also takenВҰ101966 prohibited thingsВҰ101969вҖ”stealing, deceivingВҰ101973, and put it with theirВҰ101976 own possessions.
\v 12 \add That's why\add* \add *they\add* were unable to defeat their enemiesвҖ”they had to flee from them because they took what was prohibited. I won'tВҰ101978 be with you all again unless you all destroyВҰ101991 \add вүҲwhat was taken\add*.
\v 13 \add So\add* get up and tell the peopleВҰ102007, вҖҳPurify yourselvesВҰ102009 for tomorrowВҰ102010, because \add *our\add* GodВҰ102015 YahwehВҰ102014 saysВҰ102013 that \add вүҲwe took something prohibited and we won'tВҰ102020 be able to better our enemiesВҰ102024 untilВҰ102025 it's removedВҰ102027 from among us\add*.
\v 14 \add вүҲTomorrow morningВҰ102032\add* youВҰ102031 all must present yourselves by your tribes. Then the tribe that Yahweh \add вүҲsingles out\add*, must present yourselves by your clansВҰ102041, andВҰ102031 the clan that Yahweh \add вүҲsingles out\add*, must present yourselves by household. Then the household that Yahweh \add вүҲsingles out\add*, must present yourselves individually.
\v 15 The \add >man\add* who is caughtВҰ102057 will be destroyed by fireВҰ102060, along withВҰ102058 everything that belongs to him, becauseВҰ102075 he's violated Yahweh's agreement andВҰ102056 committed a disgracefulВҰ102078 sin among YisraelВҰ102079.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Achan's Sin
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲSoВҰ102081\add* Yehoshua got up earlyВҰ102081 the next morningВҰ102083 and \add вүҲordered each tribe to come forward singly\add*, and the tribe of YehudahВҰ102091 was \add вүҲsingled out\add*.
\v 17 ThenВҰ102093 each of the clans came forward and the Zerahite clan was \add вүҲsingled out\add*, and when their familiesВҰ102107 came forwards, Zabdi'sВҰ102109 household was \add вүҲsingled out\add*.
\v 18 WhenВҰ102111 everyone in that \add вүҲextended familyВҰ102114\add* came forwardВҰ102111, AchanВҰ102117 (son of KarmiВҰ102120, son of ZabdiВҰ102123, son of ZerahВҰ102126, from the tribeВҰ102127 of YehudahВҰ102128) was \add вүҲsingled out\add*.
\v 19 ThenВҰ102130 Yehoshua told AchanВҰ102134, вҖңMy son, now \add вүҲhonour\add* YahwehВҰ102140 the godВҰ102141 of YisraelВҰ102142 andВҰ102130 giveВҰ102143 thanks to him. And tell me now what you've doneвҖ”don'tВҰ102153 hideВҰ102155 it from me.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңIt's true,вҖқ AchanВҰ102159 replied, вҖңI'veВҰ102166 sinnedВҰ102166 against YahwehВҰ102167 the godВҰ102168 of YisraelВҰ102169. This is what I did:
\v 21 I saw a \add вүҲbeautiful Babylonian cloakВҰ102177\add* and two hundred silver pieces and a tongue-shapedВҰ102184 piece of goldВҰ102185 (weighingВҰ102189 six-hundred grams) \add thereВҰ102192 inside Yericho\add*. I wanted them so I took them, and they're hiddenВҰ102193 inВҰ102176 the ground under my tent, withВҰ102176 the silver underneath.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 YehoshuaВҰ102201 sentВҰ102200 some messengersВҰ102202 and they ranВҰ102203 to the tent, and sure enough, it was all hiddenВҰ102206 there \add inВҰ102207 the ground\add* withВҰ102207 the silverВҰ102208 underneathВҰ102209.
\v 23 They tookВҰ102211 it out of the tentВҰ102213 and broughtВҰ102214 it back to Yehoshua and all the peopleВҰ102221, and spreadВҰ102223 it out in frontВҰ102224 of YahwehВҰ102225.
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ102227 Yehoshua tookВҰ102227 AchanВҰ102231 and the silverВҰ102237, the cloakВҰ102240, the goldВҰ102244 along with his children and his animals, his tentВҰ102262 and everything he owned, and took them to the Akor Valley along with all the people,
\v 25 and he saidВҰ102279, вҖңWhy did you cause trouble for us? YahwehВҰ102284 will trouble you today.вҖқ And \add вүҲthe people executed him by throwing rocks at him\add*. ThenВҰ102279 they threw rocks at them \add all\add* and burntВҰ102293 \add the bodies\add*
\v 26 and piled rocksВҰ102304 over them which are still thereВҰ102313 to this day and Yahweh'sВҰ102310 \add вүҲangerВҰ102312 subsided\add*. That's why that placeВҰ102318 is calledВҰ102316 вҖҳAkorвҖҷ \add (i.e., вҖҳTroubleвҖҷ)\add* Valley to this day.
\c 8
\s1 The defeat and destruction of Ay
\rem /s1 Ai Destroyed; The Capture and Destruction of Ai; The Israelites Defeat Ai; Ai Captured by a Stratagem and Destroyed
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ102328 told Yehoshua, вҖңDon't \add вүҲbe afraid or discouraged\add*. Take all your warriors withВҰ102351 you and go to Ay. Listen, I'veВҰ102350 givenВҰ102350 \add вүҲyou victory over\add* Ay's kingВҰ102354 and his people and his cityВҰ102361 and his land.
\v 2 You'll do to Ay and its king what you did to Yericho and its king,\f + \fr 8:2 \ft We're not actually given any details about what happened to the king of Yericho.\f* except that you all can plunder its spoil and its livestock for yourselvesВҰ102381. Ambush the city from behind.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ102386\add* Yehoshua \add вүҲled\add* his warriors towards Ay. \add *He\add* choseВҰ102394 thirtyВҰ102396 thousandВҰ102397 of the \add вүҲbravest and strongest warriors\add* and sentВҰ102401 them \add вүҲahead in the darkness\add*
\v 4 and toldВҰ102404 them, вҖңListenВҰ102405, you all lie in ambush againstВҰ102410 the city from close behindВҰ102411 \add *it\add*, and \add вүҲmake sure you all stay alert and ready\add* \add to attack\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲI will bring those warriors\add* who are withВҰ102440 me andВҰ102424 we'll approach the cityВҰ102433, thenВҰ102424 when theyВҰ102437 comeВҰ102437 out to \add вүҲattack\add* us like \add вүҲlast time\add*, we'll run back away from them.
\v 6 They'llВҰ102448 \add вүҲthink we're running away from them like we did before, so they'll chase afterВҰ102445 us untilВҰ102446 we've drawnВҰ102447 them away\add* from the cityВҰ102451.
\v 7 ThenВҰ102461 you'll all \add вүҲmove inВҰ102471\add* from your ambushВҰ102463 \add position\add* and capture the city, and your godВҰ102470 YahwehВҰ102469 \add вүҲwill give the city to you all\add*.
\v 8 \add вүҲAfter\add* you captureВҰ102474 the city, set fire to it. Do what I'veВҰ102487 orderedВҰ102487 you all \add вүҲwhich inВҰ102482 turn has come from\add* YahwehВҰ102484.
\v 9 \add вүҲSoВҰ102490\add* Yehoshua sentВҰ102490 them to \add set up\add* the ambushВҰ102495 between Ay andВҰ102490 Beyt-El (so west of Ay). \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* \add *he\add* stayed overnight \add вүҲatВҰ102507 the camp\add*.
\p
\v 10 Yehoshua got up earlyВҰ102512 in the morningВҰ102514 and gathered the \add вүҲwarriors\add*, thenВҰ102512 he and the IsraeliВҰ102521 eldersВҰ102521 went \add вүҲin frontВҰ102523 of them\add* \add to go and attack\add* Ay.
\v 11 \add *They all\add* wentВҰ102533 close to the cityВҰ102537 and campedВҰ102538 \add there slightly\add* to the northВҰ102539, with just a valley betweenВҰ102544 them and AyВҰ102540.
\v 12 (He had sent around fiveВҰ102549 thousandВҰ102550 warriors to \add вүҲlie in\add* ambushВҰ102554 between Beyt-El andВҰ102548 Ay, west of the cityВҰ102562,
\v 13 \add вүҲso\add* the main group was to the northВҰ102572 andВҰ102564 the rear guardВҰ102576 to the west.) That nightВҰ102581 Yehoshua wentВҰ102579 down into the valleyВҰ102584.
\v 14 WhenВҰ102586 the king of Ay saw \add <the Israelis\add*, he hurriedlyВҰ102591 got his men ready, and went out earlyВҰ102592 to meet YisraelВҰ102599 for the battleВҰ102600. The king and his peopleВҰ102604 went to a \add вүҲprepared spot overlooking the Yordan valley, butВҰ102586\add* he didn'tВҰ102609 know that \add вүҲanother group lay in ambushВҰ102613 behindВҰ102615 the city\add*.
\v 15 Yehoshua andВҰ102618 the Israeli group allowed themselves to be struckВҰ102618 by them, thenВҰ102618 they fled back towards the wildernessВҰ102626
\v 16 and all the \add вүҲmen\add* inВҰ102633 the city were calledВҰ102628 out to chase them. \add вүҲSoВҰ102628\add* they chased after YehoshuaВҰ102639 and were drawnВҰ102640 away from the city,
\v 17 and there wasn't a single man left inВҰ102649 Ay or Beyt-El who didn'tВҰ102645 \add вүҲjoin the chase\add*вҖ”theyВҰ102655 left the cityВҰ102661 \add wide\add* open and chased after the Israelis.
\p
\v 18 Then YahwehВҰ102669 told Yehoshua, вҖңHold your spear out \add вүҲpointing\add* towards Ay, because I will \add вүҲallow you to defeat it\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲSo\add* Yehoshua held the spear thatВҰ102675 was inВҰ102674 his hand out toward the cityВҰ102692.
\v 19 \add вүҲWhenВҰ102706 the warriors inВҰ102709 the ambushВҰ102694 saw that, they\add* rushed out from theirВҰ102697 placeВҰ102697 and entered the city and capturedВҰ102703 it, and quicklyВҰ102696 set \add *it\add* onВҰ102709 fire.
\v 20 \add WhenВҰ102711\add* the men from AyВҰ102713 turned andВҰ102711 lookedВҰ102711 behindВҰ102714 them, the smokeВҰ102718 from their cityВҰ102719 was going up into the sky, \add вүҲbutВҰ102711 they had nowhere to escape to.\add* ThenВҰ102711 \add @Yehoshua's men\add* who'd been fleeingВҰ102730 towards the wildernessВҰ102731 turned back around towards their pursuersВҰ102735
\v 21 and saw that the ambushВҰ102745 had capturedВҰ102744 the city and the smokeВҰ102751 was rising. \add вүҲSoВҰ102737\add* they \add вүҲcontinued back towards AyВҰ102740, killing their men\add*.
\v 22 \add вүҲMeanwhile,\add* \add @their warriors\add* cameВҰ102761 \add back\add* out of the cityВҰ102764, \add вүҲso\add* the men from Ay ended up inВҰ102768 the middleВҰ102768 of the two groups, andВҰ102760 \add @the Israelis\add* \add вүҲfought untilВҰ102775 they'd killed them all\add*.
\v 23 \add вүҲHowever\add* theyВҰ102788 capturedВҰ102788 the kingВҰ102786 of Ay aliveВҰ102789 andВҰ102790 broughtВҰ102790 him to Yehoshua.
\p
\v 24 ThenВҰ102796 \add вүҲafter the IsraelisВҰ102820\add* had finishedВҰ102797 killingВҰ102799 the \add вүҲmen of\add* Ay who had chased them \add towards\add* the wildernessВҰ102807, \add *they\add* returnedВҰ102819 to Ay andВҰ102796 \add вүҲslaughtered the people still inВҰ102807 there\add*,
\v 25 \add вүҲso a totalВҰ102831 of\add* twelve thousandВҰ102842 men andВҰ102830 women from AyВҰ102845 \add вүҲwere killed\add* that dayВҰ102834.
\v 26 Yehoshua didn'tВҰ102848 \add вүҲlower his\add* spear untilВҰ102855 everyone who lived inВҰ102854 Ay had been completely destroyedВҰ102857.
\v 27 \add вүҲThe Israelis\add* only took the livestock andВҰ102866 the goods from \add вүҲAy\add*, just as YahwehВҰ102873 had instructedВҰ102875 Yehoshua,
\v 28 thenВҰ102880 YehoshuaВҰ102881 burntВҰ102880 the city andВҰ102885 made itВҰ102885 a \add вүҲpermanent pile of rubble where no one lives to this dayВҰ102891\add*.
\v 29 \add *He\add* hangedВҰ102898 the kingВҰ102896 of Ay on a tree, \add вүҲbutВҰ102894\add* as the sunВҰ102907 was going down, \add *he\add* commandedВҰ102908 that the corpseВҰ102913 be brought down from the tree. They threwВҰ102917 it into the cityВҰ102923 gateway andВҰ102894 piled a big heap of rocksВҰ102928 on top of it which is still there today.
\s1 The reading of Law there at Mt. Eybal
\rem /s1 Joshua Renews the Covenant; The Lord's Covenant Renewed; The Law Is Read at Mount Ebal; The Covenant Renewed at Mount Ebal
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 30 Then Yehoshua builtВҰ102936 an altarВҰ102938 to Yisrael'sВҰ102941 godВҰ102940, YahwehВҰ102939 onВҰ102942 MtВҰ102942. Eybal\x + \xo 8:30-32: \xt Deu 27:2-8.\x*
\v 31 just like Yahweh's servantВҰ102948 Mosheh had instructedВҰ102946 \add *them\add*. (It was writtenВҰ102955 inВҰ102956 the scroll of the rules from Mosheh \add that it must be\add* an altarВҰ102959 made from whole stonesВҰ102960 that \add вүҲhaven't been chiselled withВҰ102956\add* iron tools.) Then they offered burntВҰ102970 offerings to Yahweh onВҰ102956 it, plusВҰ102968 they sacrificedВҰ102972 peaceВҰ102973 offerings,\x + \xo 8:31: \xt Exo 20:25.\x*
\v 32 andВҰ102975 \add вүҲwhile the IsraelisВҰ102989 watched,\add* \add @Yehoshua\add* inscribed onto the stones \add thereВҰ102977\add*,\f + \fr 8:32 \ft Probably not the altar stones since an iron tool wasn't allowed to be used on them.\f* a copy of the rules \add вүҲpassed on by\add* MoshehВҰ102984.
\v 33 ThenВҰ102991 all of YisraelВҰ102993 and theirВҰ103015 eldersВҰ102994 and officialsВҰ102995 and judgesВҰ102997 were standingВҰ102998 \add вүҲsome on each side\add* of the box containing Yahweh's agreement, \add вүҲfacing\add* the priestsВҰ103005 and the LevitesВҰ103006 who carriedВҰ103007 the box. Any resident foreigners were also there. Half of the people stood on the Mt. Gerazim side, and half on the Mt. Eybal side \add of the valley\add*, just like \add the way that\add* Yahweh's servantВҰ103032 MoshehВҰ103031 had originally commandedВҰ103030 for blessingВҰ103035 the people.\x + \xo 8:33-35: \xt Deu 11:29; 27:11-14.\x*
\p
\v 34 ThenВҰ103042 YehoshuaВҰ103046 read all the law, \add includingВҰ103053\add* the blessingsВҰ103052 andВҰ103053 the cursesВҰ103053, as per everythingВҰ103054 that's writtenВҰ103056 inВҰ103057 the book of the law.
\v 35 \add *He\add* \add вүҲread out every single word thatВҰ103069 MoshehВҰ103068 had written\add*, inВҰ103083 front of the entireВҰ103064 assemblyВҰ103077 of YisraelВҰ103078, includingВҰ103079 the womenВҰ103079, children, and foreigners living amongВҰ103083 them.
\c 9
\s1 The Gibeonites deceive Yehoshua
\rem /s1 The Gibeonites Save Themselves by Trickery; The Gibeonite Deception; The Gibeonites Deceive Israel; The Gibeonites Deceive Joshua
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲThere were several kingsВҰ103090 who ruled in regions onВҰ103092 this west side of the YordanВҰ103093вҖ”the HittitesВҰ103104 and AmoritesВҰ103105, the CanaanitesВҰ103106 and PerizzitesВҰ103107, the HivitesВҰ103108 and the Yebusites. Some were in the hill countryВҰ103094, some in the lowlandsВҰ103095, and some along the Mediterranean coastВҰ103097 south of LebanonВҰ103103\add*. \add When\add* \add *they\add* heardВҰ103087 about \add @what had happened atВҰ103092 Ay\add*,
\v 2 theyВҰ103111 \add вүҲformed an alliance\add* to fightВҰ103113 \add togetherВҰ103112\add* against YehoshuaВҰ103116 andВҰ103117 YisraelВҰ103119.
\p
\v 3 \add вүҲHowever,\add* when \add the people who\add* live in GibeonВҰ103125 heardВҰ103126 what Yehoshua had done to YerichoВҰ103131 and Ay,
\v 4 they \add вүҲdecided to use cunningВҰ103138\add* \add instead\add*. They \add вүҲfound old, worn-out sacksВҰ103142 to throw over theirВҰ103144 donkeysВҰ103144 and old, worn-out wineskins that had been torn and mendedВҰ103149, thenВҰ103134 sent men to act as ambassadorsВҰ103140\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲThey found worn-out sandalsВҰ103151 that had been patchedВҰ103153, and wore worn-out clothesВҰ103155.\add* All the \add вүҲfood that they took for the journey was already dry and disintegrating into crumbsВҰ103163\add*.
\v 6 They wentВҰ103165 to Yehoshua in the campВҰ103171 at GilgalВҰ103172 and told him, вҖңWe've comeВҰ103181 from a far-off land and \add вүҲwant you to make a treaty with\add* us.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 An IsraeliВҰ103190 manВҰ103190 asked the Hivite \add (because Gilead was inВҰ103197 the Hivite region)\add*, вҖңPerhaps you really live near by? How could we make a treaty withВҰ103197 you?вҖқ\x + \xo 9:7: \xt Exo 23:32; 34:12; Deu 7:2.\x*
\p
\v 8 They \add вүҲaddressed\add* Yehoshua, вҖңWe are yourВҰ103211 servantsВҰ103211.вҖқ
\p Yehoshua \add вүҲasked\add* them, вҖңWho are you? And whereВҰ103218 have you comeВҰ103219 from?вҖқ
\p
\v 9 вҖңYour servantsВҰ103227 have comeВҰ103226 from a very distantВҰ103224 land,вҖқ they replied, вҖңbecauseВҰ103228 of the reputation of your godВҰ103230, YahwehВҰ103229. We've heardВҰ103233 the \add #reports\add* about himВҰ103234 andВҰ103221 everything that heВҰ103239 did inВҰ103240 EgyptВҰ103240,
\v 10 and everything that he did to the twoВҰ103248 AmoriteВҰ103250 kingsВҰ103249 onВҰ103252 the otherВҰ103252 side of the YordanВҰ103253вҖ”King SihonВҰ103254 of HeshbonВҰ103256, and King OgВҰ103257 of the BashanВҰ103260 who \add вүҲlived\add* inВҰ103252 AshtarothВҰ103262.\x + \xo 9:10: \xt Num 21:21-35.\x*
\v 11 \add вүҲSoВҰ103264\add* our eldersВҰ103266 and all those who live inВҰ103273 our area instructed us, вҖҳTake provisionsВҰ103274 for the \add вүҲjourneyВҰ103275\add* and goВҰ103276 to meet them, and tell them, вҖңWe are yourВҰ103273 servantsВҰ103280. \add вүҲNow make a treaty withВҰ103273\add* us.вҖқ вҖҷ
\v 12 ThisВҰ103293 breadВҰ103290 of ours was warm \add вүҲfrom our ovens\add* when we loaded it \add вүҲfor our journey\add*, and now, look, it's \add all\add* dry and crumblingВҰ103303.
\v 13 And these wineskins were new when weВҰ103309 filledВҰ103309 them, and look, \add now\add* they're \add all\add* torn. \add вүҲSame with\add* our clothesВҰ103314 and our sandalsВҰ103315вҖ”they're \add all\add* worn-out from the very \add вүҲlongВҰ103317 journeyВҰ103318\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 14 The \add вүҲIsraeli leaders tasted\add* some of theirВҰ103323 provisionsВҰ103323, butВҰ103321 they didn'tВҰ103328 ask YahwehВҰ103327 \add вүҲfor advice\add*.
\v 15 \add вүҲSoВҰ103331\add* Yehoshua \add вүҲagreed to\add* make peaceВҰ103334 with them, and theyВҰ103339 made a treaty \add вүҲnot to attack their people\add*, and all the Israeli leadersВҰ103341 promised that.
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲHowever, threeВҰ103346 daysВҰ103347 afterВҰ103348 making the treaty, they discovered that those people actually lived quite close to where they were\add*.
\v 17 ThenВҰ103364 the IsraelisВҰ103367 wentВҰ103368 on forward and they arrived at those cities on the thirdВҰ103373 dayвҖ”the cities of GibeonВҰ103375, KefirahВҰ103376, BeerotВҰ103377, and Kiryat-Yearim.
\v 18 ButВҰ103381 \add *they\add* didn'tВҰ103381 \add вүҲattackВҰ103382 those cities\add* because \add *their\add* leaders had made a promise by the godВҰ103392 of YisraelВҰ103384, YahwehВҰ103391.
\p \add вүҲAllВҰ103393 the IsraelisВҰ103384\add* grumbledВҰ103394 against their leaders for making that treaty,
\v 19 \add вүҲbutВҰ103402\add* their leadersВҰ103405 told \add *them\add*, вҖңWeВҰ103416 ourselves have promisedВҰ103412 them by \add *our\add* GodВҰ103415 YahwehВҰ103414 \add вүҲso\add* now we can'tВҰ103418 touchВҰ103420 them.
\v 20 We're \add вүҲforced now to let them liveВҰ103426, otherwise God's angerВҰ103432 would be against us for breaking our promise\add* to them.
\v 21 \add вүҲSoВҰ103441\add* we'll let them liveВҰ103444 \add butВҰ103441 make them our slaves\add*.вҖқ \add вүҲAs a result of that,\add* \add @the Gibeonites\add* became woodcutters andВҰ103441 water-carriersВҰ103450 for all the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ103459 Yehoshua summoned them andВҰ103459 asked them, вҖңWhy did you all deceiveВҰ103466 us \add вүҲby telling us that you lived far away when really you were very close\add*?
\v 23 \add вүҲBecause of that,\add* you're all cursedВҰ103478 and you'll always be our slavesВҰ103484вҖ”you'll all be the woodcutters and water-carriersВҰ103489 for the houseВҰ103490 of my godВҰ103491.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 вҖңBecause it was \add вүҲmade very clear\add* to your servantsВҰ103501,вҖқ they answeredВҰ103493, вҖңthat your godВҰ103506 YahwehВҰ103505 had commandedВҰ103504 his servantВҰ103510 MoshehВҰ103509 to giveВҰ103511 to you all the land andВҰ103493 to destroyВҰ103518 everyone who lives in the region. \add вүҲWe fearedВҰ103526 for our lives when you came closer\add*, so that's what we did.
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ103536 now we're inВҰ103538 your powerвҖ”do to us whatever you think\add* is goodВҰ103539 andВҰ103536 rightВҰ103540.вҖқ
\v 26 \add вүҲSoВҰ103546\add* that's what \add @Yehoshua\add* did andВҰ103546 he \add вүҲprevented the IsraelisВҰ103554\add* from killing them.
\v 27 \add вүҲInsteadВҰ103559\add* \add *he\add* made them \add вүҲmove to where he wanted, to become\add* woodcutters and water-carriersВҰ103565 for the people and for Yahweh'sВҰ103568 altarВҰ103567 untilВҰ103569 this day.
\c 10
\s1 The defeat of the Amorites
\rem /s1 The Amorites Are Defeated; The Sun Stands Still; The conquest of the south; Israel Defeats the Southern Kings
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲOnce\add* KingВҰ103585 AdoniВҰ103582-TsedekВҰ103584 of YerushalemВҰ103586 heard that Yehoshua had capturedВҰ103589 Ay and completely destroyedВҰ103594 it, and that he'd treated the king of Ay the same as he had treated the king of YerichoВҰ103597, and he heard that the Gibeonites had made peace withВҰ103612 YisraelВҰ103610 and were \add now working for\add* them,
\v 2 \add @the people of Yerushalem\add* were very afraidВҰ103614 becauseВҰ103623 GibeonВҰ103619 had been a powerful cityВҰ103617, stronger than Ay, andВҰ103614 all it's warriorsВҰ103632 were powerful.
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ103634\add* King AdoniВҰ103635-TsedekВҰ103637 sentВҰ103634 to King HohamВҰ103642 of HebronВҰ103645, King PiramВҰ103648 of Yarmut, King YafiaВҰ103654 of Lakish, andВҰ103634 King DebirВҰ103660 of EglonВҰ103663, saying,
\v 4 вҖңCome \add вүҲhere\add* and helpВҰ103669 me. We'll attackВҰ103670 GibeonВҰ103673 because they've made peaceВҰ103676 with Yehoshua and \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ103683\add*.вҖқ
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ103685\add* those fiveВҰ103687 AmoriteВҰ103690 kingsВҰ103689 (from YerushalemВҰ103692, HebronВҰ103695, Yarmut, Lakish, and EglonВҰ103704) joined together to go to GibeonВҰ103712 and theirВҰ103708 \add armiesВҰ103708\add* campedВҰ103709 there to fight againstВҰ103714 itВҰ103714.
\p
\v 6 The \add вүҲleaders\add* of GibeonВҰ103718 \add hurriedly\add* sentВҰ103716 to Yehoshua in the campВҰ103724 at GilgalВҰ103725, saying, вҖңDon't \add вүҲabandon\add* yourВҰ103730 servantsВҰ103731. Come quicklyВҰ103734 and helpВҰ103737 us, and saveВҰ103735 us because all the kingsВҰ103743 of the AmoritesВҰ103744 who live in the hill countryВҰ103746 have combined againstВҰ103740 us.вҖқ
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ103748\add* YehoshuaВҰ103749 and his warriors and prize fightersВҰ103757 \add вүҲheaded off\add* from GilgalВҰ103752,
\v 8 and YahwehВҰ103765 told \add *him\add*, вҖңDon'tВҰ103768 be afraidВҰ103771 of them, because \add вүҲyou'll have the victory over them\add*вҖ”none of them will be able to standВҰ103778 against you.вҖқ
\p
\v 9 Yehoshua \add and his men\add* spent the nightВҰ103789 moving in, and thenВҰ103783 \add вүҲsurprised the alliance\add*,
\v 10 and YahwehВҰ103796 confusedВҰ103795 them \add вүҲas the Israelis approached\add* and \add caused them\add* to be badly defeatedВҰ103799 atВҰ103803 GibeonВҰ103803. ThenВҰ103795 \add #they\add* chased them onВҰ103803 the road going to Beyt-HoronВҰ103809 and killed them as far as AzekahВҰ103813 and MakkedahВҰ103816.
\v 11 As they fled from the Israelis on the slope down from Beyt-HoronВҰ103827 heading towards AzekahВҰ103838, YahwehВҰ103828 hurled largeВҰ103832 hailstones down on them from the sky andВҰ103818 they diedвҖ”\add actually\add* more of them died from the hail than were killedВҰ103847 withВҰ103819 swordsВҰ103850 by the \add вүҲIsraelis\add*.
\p
\v 12 Then Yehoshua spokeВҰ103854 to YahwehВҰ103859 onВҰ103871 the dayВҰ103857 that \add вүҲhe gave them victory over the AmoritesВҰ103862\add*, and \add вүҲinВҰ103871 frontВҰ103863 of the IsraelisВҰ103865\add* he saidВҰ103866,
\q1 вҖңSun, stay stillВҰ103872 over GibeonВҰ103871,
\q1 вүҲand moonВҰ103873, over the Ayyalon Valley.
\m
\v 13 ThenВҰ103877 the sun stood still and the moonВҰ103879 stood still untilВҰ103881 the nationВҰ103884 had avengedВҰ103883 themselves of their enemiesВҰ103885. (Isn't that writtenВҰ103889 aboutВҰ103902 in the Jashar scrollВҰ103892? The sun stood still in the middleВҰ103896 of the sky and it didn'tВҰ103886 hurry to go around for almost a whole dayВҰ103902.\x + \xo 10:13: \xt 2Sam 1:18.\x*
\v 14 ThereВҰ103916 had never beforeВҰ103909 been a dayВҰ103907 like that, andВҰ103905 nothing like it sinceВҰ103910 thenВҰ103905, when YahwehВҰ103912 listenedВҰ103911 to a man's voiceВҰ103913, because \add *he\add* was fightingВҰ103917 for YisraelВҰ103918.)
\p
\v 15 Then Yehoshua and all YisraelВҰ103925 returnedВҰ103921 to their campВҰ103929 at GilgalВҰ103930.
\s1 Five Amorite kings defeated
\rem /s1 Five Amorite Kings Killed; Five Kings Defeated; Joshua Kills the Five Southern Kings; Joshua Captures the Five Amorite Kings
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 16 \add вүҲMeanwhile\add* those fiveВҰ103933 kingsВҰ103934 had fled away andВҰ103936 hiddenВҰ103936 atВҰ103937 MakkedahВҰ103938 inВҰ103937 a cave,
\v 17 andВҰ103940 Yehoshua was told, вҖңThe fiveВҰ103944 kingsВҰ103945 have been foundВҰ103943 hiding inВҰ103947 the cave atВҰ103947 MakkedahВҰ103948.вҖқ
\v 18 Yehoshua saidВҰ103950, вҖңRoll largeВҰ103954 rocksВҰ103953 across the mouthВҰ103957 of the cave andВҰ103959 assign menВҰ103961 to guardВҰ103962 them there,
\v 19 butВҰ103964 \add the rest of you,\add* don'tВҰ103965 stay there. Chase afterВҰ103969 your enemiesВҰ103970 andВҰ103964 attackВҰ103971 them from behind. Don't let them get into theirВҰ103979 citiesВҰ103979, because your godВҰ103983 YahwehВҰ103982 \add вүҲwants you all to defeat them\add*.
\v 20 \add вүҲSoВҰ103986\add* YehoshuaВҰ103988 and \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ103990\add* finishedВҰ103987 \add вүҲmost of them off\add*, although \add вүҲsome did manage to escape and get back\add* into their fortifiedВҰ104006 citiesВҰ104005.
\v 21 ThenВҰ104008 all the peopleВҰ104011 returnedВҰ104008 to Yehoshua inВҰ104019 the campВҰ104014 atВҰ104019 MakkedahВҰ104018. \add After that,\add* no one dared to criticise the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ104024\add*.
\p
\v 22 ThenВҰ104030 Yehoshua saidВҰ104030, вҖңOpen up the cave andВҰ104037 bringВҰ104037 those fiveВҰ104041 kingsВҰ104042 to me.вҖқ
\v 23 They did it and broughtВҰ104050 the five kings out from the caveвҖ”the kings of YerushalemВҰ104063, HebronВҰ104067, Yarmut, Lakish, and EglonВҰ104079.
\v 24 \add вүҲWhenВҰ104081\add* they took them to Yehoshua, he summoned \add вүҲall the warriorsВҰ104102\add* andВҰ104081 told the commandersВҰ104101, вҖңCome over here. Put your feet on the necks of these kings.вҖқ
\v 25 ThenВҰ104125 heВҰ104138 told them, вҖңDon't be afraidВҰ104130 and don'tВҰ104128 be dismayedВҰ104133. Be strongВҰ104134 and courageousВҰ104135, because this is what YahwehВҰ104139 will do to all yourВҰ104142 enemiesВҰ104142вҖ”\add вүҲincludingВҰ104131 the ones that youВҰ104144 all still have\add* to fightВҰ104145.вҖқ
\v 26 ThenВҰ104148 YehoshuaВҰ104149 executed \add @the five kings\add* andВҰ104148 hangedВҰ104159 them on five trees, \add вүҲwhere their bodies were left\add* untilВҰ104163 eveningВҰ104165.
\v 27 AsВҰ104173 the sunВҰ104171 was goingВҰ104170 down, \add *he\add* commandedВҰ104172 that \add @the bodies\add* be brought down and thrown into the cave whereВҰ104181 they had hiddenВҰ104182, and they placedВҰ104185 largeВҰ104187 rocksВҰ104186 over the cave entrance \add again, which are still thereВҰ104184\add* to this dayВҰ104195.
\s1 Yehoshua attacks more Amorites
\rem /s1 Israel Destroys the Southern Cities; Joshua Captures More Amorite Territory
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 28 Then Yehoshua capturedВҰ104202 Makkedah that \add same\add* dayВҰ104204. \add #They\add* killed \add вүҲthe king and everyoneВҰ104217 else inВҰ104222 the city\add*, leaving no survivorsВҰ104225, and \add @Yehoshua\add* did the same to the king of Makkedah as he'd done to the king of Yericho.\f + \fr 10:28 \ft We're not actually given any details about what happened to the king of Yericho.\f*
\rem /s1 Southern Cities Conquered
\p
\v 29 ThenВҰ104234 Yehoshua and all YisraelВҰ104238 went \add southwest\add* from MakkedahВҰ104240 to LibnahВҰ104241 and foughtВҰ104242 against \add *it\add*.
\v 30 YahwehВҰ104248 also \add вүҲallowed YisraelВҰ104253 to conquer\add* it and its king, and \add @Yehoshua\add* \add again\add* \add вүҲkilled everyoneВҰ104264 inВҰ104252 the city\add*, leaving no survivorsВҰ104274, and he did the same to the king of Libnah as he'd done to the king of YerichoВҰ104280.
\p
\v 31 Then Yehoshua and all YisraelВҰ104287 went \add south\add* from LibnahВҰ104289 to Lakish, \add вүҲwhere\add* they took a position against \add @the city\add* and foughtВҰ104293 against it.
\v 32 On the secondВҰ104305 dayВҰ104304 \add of the battle\add*, YahwehВҰ104297 \add вүҲhelped YisraelВҰ104302 defeat Lakish\add*, and \add #they\add* capturedВҰ104303 it and \add вүҲkilled everyoneВҰ104312 inВҰ104301 the city\add* like \add #they\add* had done to LibnahВҰ104322.
\v 33 KingВҰ104328 HoramВҰ104327 of GezerВҰ104329 arrived to helpВҰ104330 Lakish, \add вүҲbutВҰ104334\add* Yehoshua defeatedВҰ104334 himВҰ104334 and his men, leaving no survivorsВҰ104345.
\p
\v 34 ThenВҰ104347 Yehoshua and \add вүҲthe Israelis\add* went \add west\add* from Lakish to EglonВҰ104354, \add вүҲwhere\add* they took a position against \add @the city\add* and foughtВҰ104357 against it.
\v 35 That day \add #they\add* capturedВҰ104360 it andВҰ104360 \add вүҲkilled everyoneВҰ104368 inВҰ104373 the city\add* like \add #they\add* had done to Lakish.
\p
\v 36 Then Yehoshua and \add вүҲthe Israelis\add* went \add west\add* from EglonВҰ104390 up \add into the hills\add* to HebronВҰ104391, and foughtВҰ104392 againstВҰ104393 it.
\v 37 They capturedВҰ104395 it and killed the kingВҰ104403 and everyone inВҰ104416 all their \add вүҲtowns\add*, leaving no survivorsВҰ104420 the same as EglonВҰ104425.
\p
\v 38 Then Yehoshua and \add вүҲthe Israelis\add* went to \add the city of\add* DebirВҰ104444 and foughtВҰ104445 againstВҰ104446 it.
\v 39 They capturedВҰ104448 \add @the city\add* and its king and all their \add вүҲtowns\add*, killing everyoneВҰ104464 and leaving no survivorsВҰ104472. \add #They\add* treated DebirВҰ104479 and its king just like they had to LibnahВҰ104483 and HebronВҰ104475 and their kings.
\p
\v 40 \add вүҲSoВҰ104486\add* Yehoshua \add вүҲattacked and conquered the entireВҰ104490 region\add*вҖ”the hill countryВҰ104493 and the NegevВҰ104494, the lowlandsВҰ104495 and the slopesВҰ104496, and all theirВҰ104500 kingsВҰ104500. He didn'tВҰ104501 leave any survivorsВҰ104503 \add вүҲbutВҰ104486\add* destroyedВҰ104508 everythingВҰ104505 living, just as Yisrael'sВҰ104513 godВҰ104512 YahwehВҰ104511 had commandedВҰ104510.
\v 41 Yehoshua \add вүҲattacked and conquered\add* them from Kadesh-Barnea and as far as GazaВҰ104521, all the land of GoshenВҰ104526 and as far as GibeonВҰ104529.
\v 42 In one swoop, Yehoshua capturedВҰ104539 all those kingsВҰ104534 andВҰ104531 theirВҰ104538 land, because Yisrael'sВҰ104546 godВҰ104545 YahwehВҰ104544 had fought for Yisrael.
\v 43 ThenВҰ104550 Yehoshua andВҰ104552 \add вүҲhis warriors\add* returnedВҰ104550 to their campВҰ104558 at GilgalВҰ104559.
\c 11
\s1 Yehoshua defeats the northern kings
\rem /s1 Joshua Defeats Jabin and His Allies; The conquest of the north; Israel Defeats the Northern Kings; The United Kings of Northern Canaan Defeated; Northern Kings Defeated
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲNow when\add* King YabinВҰ104564 of Hatsor heardВҰ104563 \add <about all that\add*, he sentВҰ104568 to King Yovav of MadonВҰ104573 and the kings of ShimronВҰ104577 and Akshaf,
\v 2 as well as the kingsВҰ104585 from the hill countryВҰ104588 in the northВҰ104587 and in \add вүҲthe rift valley plains\add* southВҰ104590 of Lake Galilee, and in the lowlandsВҰ104592 and in the heightsВҰ104593 of DorВҰ104594 in the west,
\v 3 and \add вүЎthe kings of\add* the Canaanites both east and west, and the AmoritesВҰ104600, HittitesВҰ104601, PerizzitesВҰ104602, and the Yebusites who lived in the hill countryВҰ104604, and to the HivitesВҰ104605 by \add Mt.\add* HermonВҰ104607 in the Mitspah regionВҰ104608.
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ104611\add* they \add all\add* came out with theirВҰ104615 warriorsвҖ”so many peopleВҰ104617 thatВҰ104621 they were as many as the \add grains of\add* sand on the seashore, along with many horsesВҰ104628 andВҰ104611 chariotsВҰ104629.
\v 5 All those kingsВҰ104636 gatheredВҰ104634 togetherВҰ104640 at the time they'd specified andВҰ104634 took up positions at the MeromВҰ104644 stream to fightВҰ104645 against YisraelВҰ104648.
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲButВҰ104651\add* YahwehВҰ104652 told Yehoshua, вҖңDon't be afraidВҰ104658 that \add вүҲthey look overwhelming\add*, because tomorrowВҰ104662 atВҰ104681 this timeВҰ104663, I'llВҰ104665 \add вүҲensure that they're all slainВҰ104670 by\add* YisraelВҰ104672. You'll hamstringВҰ104676 their horsesВҰ104675 and burnВҰ104680 their chariotsВҰ104679.вҖқ
\v 7 ThenВҰ104683 YehoshuaВҰ104684 and all \add вүҲhis warriors\add* wentВҰ104683 to MeromВҰ104694 and attacked them \add вүҲwithout warning\add*
\v 8 andВҰ104699 YahwehВҰ104700 \add вүҲenabled them to defeatВҰ104704 them\add*.
\v 9 ThenВҰ104727 YehoshuaВҰ104729 did \add вүҲwhat YahwehВҰ104734 had instructed\add* himвҖ”he crippled their horsesВҰ104737 andВҰ104727 set fireВҰ104743 to their chariotsВҰ104741.
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲAfter that,\add* Yehoshua returned to Hatsor \add city\add* and capturedВҰ104750 it and killed the kingВҰ104756вҖ”inВҰ104748 the past it had been the headВҰ104764 of all those kingdomsВҰ104767.
\v 11 TheyВҰ104790 killed everythingВҰ104773 inВҰ104778 \add @the city\add*вҖ”not leaving anything that breathesВҰ104787вҖ”andВҰ104770 thenВҰ104770 set fireВҰ104792 to it.
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲSoВҰ104794\add* YehoshuaВҰ104808 \add had\add* capturedВҰ104807 all those kings and their citiesВҰ104798, and completely destroyedВҰ104813 \add @them and their people\add* just as Yahweh'sВҰ104819 servantВҰ104818 MoshehВҰ104817 had commandedВҰ104816.
\v 13 \add However,\add* other than Hatsor, they didn'tВҰ104829 burnВҰ104830 any of the \add other more defensible\add* citiesВҰ104824 built \add up\add* on moundsВҰ104828.
\v 14 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ104848\add* took any valuables and any livestockВҰ104844 from those citiesВҰ104842, butВҰ104840 they killed everyoneВҰ104847 and everything else.
\v 15 Yehoshua did everything exactly as YahwehВҰ104871 had instructed his servantВҰ104875 Mosheh (andВҰ104883 as Mosheh had then instructed him), not \add вүҲforgetting or ignoring\add* anythingВҰ104889.
\s1 Yehoshua controls the entire region
\rem /s1 Summary of Joshua's Conquests; The Territory Taken by Joshua
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 16 YehoshuaВҰ104900 conquered the whole regionвҖ”the hill country and all the NegevВҰ104912, all of the GoshenВҰ104917 region, the lowlands and \add вүҲthe rift valley plains\add*, the hill country of YisraelВҰ104927 and its lowlands
\v 17 from Mt. HalakВҰ104933 downhill towards SeirВҰ104935, and as far as BaalВҰ104938-GadВҰ104939 inВҰ104940 the LebanonВҰ104941 valleyВҰ104940 below Mt. HermonВҰ104945. He attacked and capturedВҰ104950 all theirВҰ104949 kingsВҰ104949 and executed them.
\v 18 YehoshuaВҰ104957 had spent \add вүҲquite some time\add* battlingВҰ104964 with those kingsВҰ104962.
\v 19 No cityВҰ104969 made peaceВҰ104971 withВҰ104984 \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ104975\add* exceptВҰ104976 for the HivitesВҰ104977 who lived in GibeonВҰ104979вҖ”all the rest were taken in battleВҰ104984
\v 20 because itВҰ104990 was Yahweh who'd \add вүҲmade them stubborn\add* so they'd fight against YisraelВҰ104999 and be completely destroyed without any \add вүҲmercy\add*. \add Yes,\add* they were annihilated just as Yahweh had instructedВҰ105011 MoshehВҰ105015.\x + \xo 11:20: \xt Deu 7:16.\x*
\p
\v 21 At that time, Yehoshua \add also\add* wentВҰ105018 and exterminated the AnakitesВҰ105025 from the hill country, from HebronВҰ105031, DebirВҰ105034, Anab, and all the hill country of YehudahВҰ105040 and YisraelВҰ105043. \add *He\add* completely destroyedВҰ105047 them from theirВҰ105046 citiesВҰ105046.
\v 22 No \add вүҲdescendants of Anak\add* were left in YisraelВҰ105056, except that \add some\add* remainedВҰ105061 in GazaВҰ105058, in GatВҰ105059, and in AshdodВҰ105060.
\p
\v 23 Yehoshua captured the entireВҰ105067 region, just as YahwehВҰ105073 had told MoshehВҰ105076, and Yehoshua gaveВҰ105077 it as an inheritanceВҰ105079 to YisraelВҰ105080, divided into portions according to their tribesВҰ105082, and thenВҰ105063 the region \add вүҲwas peacefulВҰ105084\add*.
\c 12
\s1 The kings defeated by Mosheh
\rem /s1 Kings Defeated East of the Jordan; The Kings Conquered by Moses; The Kings Defeated by Moses; List of Defeated Kings
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 TheseВҰ105113 are the kingsВҰ105090 in the regionВҰ105100 who the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ105096 defeatedВҰ105093\add* onВҰ105101 the eastern side of the YordanВҰ105102 \add river\add* and tookВҰ105097 possessionВҰ105097 of theirВҰ105100 land from the ArnonВҰ105106 riverbed \add in the south\add* to MtВҰ105109. HermonВҰ105110 \add in the north\add*, includingВҰ105088 all of the eastern \add вүҲrift valley plains\add*:\x + \xo 12:1-5: \xt Num 21:21-35; Deu 2:26вҖ“3:11.\x*
\v 2 KingВҰ105117 Sihon of the AmoritesВҰ105118 who livedВҰ105119 inВҰ105120 HeshbonВҰ105120 and ruledВҰ105121 \add over\add* AroerВҰ105122 (onВҰ105120 the edge of the ArnonВҰ105129 riverbed) and \add over\add* half of GileadВҰ105133 up to the YabbokВҰ105135 riverbed \add whichВҰ105123 formed\add* the borderВҰ105137 withВҰ105120 the AmmonitesВҰ105139,
\v 3 as well as the \add вүҲeasternВҰ105146 rift valley plains\add* down to Lake Galilee and to the Sea of ArabahВҰ105149 (\add also called\add* the Dead Sea or the Salt Sea), the road to Beyt-Yeshimot and the area southwardВҰ105157 below the slopesВҰ105159 of \add Mt.\add* PisgahВҰ105160.
\p
\v 4 \add The Israelis also defeated\add* KingВҰ105164 OgВҰ105163 from BashanВҰ105165, \add вүҲone of the few remaining\add* Refa'ites, who livedВҰ105168 inВҰ105169 AshtarotВҰ105169 andВҰ105170 atВҰ105169 EdreiВҰ105170,
\v 5 and ruledВҰ105172 over MtВҰ105173. HermonВҰ105174, SalekahВҰ105175, all of BashanВҰ105178 to the border of the GeshuritesВҰ105182 and MaacathitesВҰ105183, as well as half of GileadВҰ105185 to the border withВҰ105173 KingВҰ105188 SihonВҰ105187 from HeshbonВҰ105190.
\p
\v 6 Yahweh's servant Mosheh and the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ105197\add* had \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ105198 them\add* and Mosheh had given \add @that region\add* as a possessionВҰ105204 to the \add descendants of\add* Reuben and Gad and to the half-tribe of MenashshehВҰ105209.\x + \xo 12:6: \xt Num 32:33; Deu 3:12.\x*
\s1 The kings defeated by Yehoshua
\rem /s1 Kings Defeated West of the Jordan; The Kings Defeated by Joshua; The Kings Conquered by Joshua
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 7 These are the kingsВҰ105213 in the region that Yehoshua and the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ105219 defeatedВҰ105216\add* onВҰ105220 the western side of the YordanВҰ105221 \add river\add* from Baal-GadВҰ105224 in the LebanonВҰ105226 valleyВҰ105225 to MtВҰ105229. HalakВҰ105230 whichВҰ105231 goesВҰ105231 up towardВҰ105232 SeirВҰ105232 \add (Edom)\add*. Yehoshua \add вүҲdivided up\add* \add @that region\add* as a possessionВҰ105237 to the \add various\add* tribesВҰ105235 of YisraelВҰ105219,
\v 8 as well as the hill countryВҰ105240, the lowlandsВҰ105241, the \add вүҲrift valley\add*, the slopesВҰ105243, the wildernessВҰ105244 and the NegevВҰ105245вҖ”\add the land of\add* the HittitesВҰ105246, AmoritesВҰ105247, CanaanitesВҰ105248, PerizzitesВҰ105249, HivitesВҰ105250, and the YebusitesВҰ105251:
\v 9 the king of YerichoВҰ105255, the king of AyВҰ105258 (near Beyt-El),
\v 10 the king of YerushalemВҰ105268, the king of HebronВҰ105271,
\v 11 the king of Yarmut, the king of Lakish,
\v 12 the king of EglonВҰ105282, the king of GezerВҰ105285,
\v 13 the king of DebirВҰ105289, the king of GederВҰ105292,
\v 14 the king of HormahВҰ105296, the king of AradВҰ105299,
\v 15 the king of LibhahВҰ105303, the king of AdullamВҰ105306,
\v 16 the king of MakkedahВҰ105310, the king of Beyt-El,
\v 17 the king of TappuahВҰ105319, the king of HeferВҰ105322,
\v 18 the king of AfekВҰ105326, the king of LasharonВҰ105329,
\v 19 the king of MadonВҰ105333, the king of HatsorВҰ105336,
\v 20 the king of ShimronВҰ105341 Meron, the king of Akshaf,
\v 21 the king of TaanachВҰ105348, the king of MegiddoВҰ105351,
\v 22 the king of KedeshВҰ105355, the king of YokneamВҰ105359 in KarmelВҰ105360,
\v 23 the king of Dor of Nafoth Dor, the king of GoyimВҰ105370 in GilgalВҰ105371,
\v 24 andВҰ105381 the kingВҰ105374 of TirzahВҰ105375вҖ”a totalВҰ105377 of thirty-oneВҰ105380 kingsВҰ105379.
\c 13
\s1 The regions not yet captured
\rem /s1 The Land Still to Be Taken; Land Still to Be Taken; The Land Yet to Be Conquered; The Parts of Canaan Still Unconquered
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Now the yearsВҰ105394 had passed and Yehoshua had grown old, and YahwehВҰ105389 saidВҰ105388 to him, вҖңYou're old \add now\add* and \add вүҲthere's still a lot of land that needs to be captured\add*.
\v 2 This is the remainingВҰ105404 land: all the territoriesВҰ105407 of the PhilistinesВҰ105408, and all of the GeshuritesВҰ105411,
\v 3 from ShihorВҰ105415 (\add вүҲeast\add* of EgyptВҰ105421) and as far as the borderВҰ105423 of Ekron to the northВҰ105425 (it's considered to be CanaaniteВҰ105426), the fiveВҰ105428 rulersВҰ105430 of the PhilistinesВҰ105431 (in GazaВҰ105432, AshdodВҰ105433, AshkelonВҰ105434, GatВҰ105435, and Ekron), and the AvvitesВҰ105437.
\v 4 In the southВҰ105439: all the land of the CanaanitesВҰ105443, and a Mearah thatВҰ105445 \add belongsВҰ105446 to\add* the SidoniansВҰ105446, as far as AfekВҰ105449, as far as the borderВҰ105451 of the AmoritesВҰ105452,
\v 5 plusВҰ105456 the land of the GebalitesВҰ105455, all LebanonВҰ105458 towards the east, from BaalВҰ105461-GadВҰ105462 below MtВҰ105464. HermonВҰ105466 as far as LeboВҰ105468-HamathВҰ105469.
\v 6 I myself will \add вүҲdriveВҰ105486 out\add* all those who live inВҰ105493 the hill countryВҰ105474 from LebanonВҰ105477 as far as MisrefotВҰ105480-Maim, and all the SidoniansВҰ105484. \add вүҲMake sure that it's given\add* to \add вүҲthe IsraelisВҰ105489\add* as an inheritanceВҰ105493, just as I instructedВҰ105495 you.\x + \xo 13:6: \xt Num 33:54.\x*
\v 7 AllВҰ105499 that land should be divided up as an inheritanceВҰ105503 for the nineВҰ105504 tribesВҰ105505 plusВҰ105506 \add half of \add* the half-tribe of MenashshehВҰ105508.
\s1 Division of the land east of the Yordan
\rem /s1 The Land Divided East of the Jordan; Division of the Land East of the Jordan; Land distributed east of Jordan; The Division of the Territory East of the Jordan; The Territory East of the Jordan
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲAlong withВҰ105519 the other\add* \add half of \add* the half-tribe of Menashsheh, the \add вүҲtribes of Reuben andВҰ105512 Gad\add* had taken theirВҰ105514 inheritanceВҰ105514 onВҰ105519 the other (easternВҰ105521) side of the YordanВҰ105520 as \add вүҲapproved\add* by Yahweh'sВҰ105527 servantВҰ105526 Mosheh,\x + \xo 13:8: \xt Num 32:33; Deu 3:12.\x*
\v 9 from Aroer, which is on the edge of the ArnonВҰ105536 riverbed, and the cityВҰ105537 that's in the middleВҰ105539 of the valleyВҰ105541, and all the plateauВҰ105544 \add вүҲnear\add* MedebaВҰ105545, to DibonВҰ105548.
\v 10 \add Also,\add* all the citiesВҰ105551 of KingВҰ105553 SihonВҰ105552 of the AmoritesВҰ105554 who ruled inВҰ105557 HeshbonВҰ105557, as far as the borderВҰ105560 withВҰ105557 the AmmonitesВҰ105562,
\v 11 and GileadВҰ105564, and the territoryВҰ105565 of the GeshuritesВҰ105566 and the MaacathitesВҰ105567, and all MtВҰ105569. HermonВҰ105570, and all the BashanВҰ105573 as far as SalekahВҰ105576,
\v 12 all the kingdomВҰ105580 of OgВҰ105581 in the BashanВҰ105582, who reignedВҰ105585 in AshtarothВҰ105586 and in EdreiВҰ105587 (what remained from the remnantВҰ105590 of the Refa'itesВҰ105591). MoshehВҰ105593 \add вүҲhad attacked them and captured their lands\add*.
\v 13 \add вүҲButВҰ105596\add* the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* didn'tВҰ105596 \add вүҲcapture the land of\add* the GeshuritesВҰ105607 or the MaacathitesВҰ105608 andВҰ105596 \add вүҲso those peoplesВҰ105598\add* live \add вүҲamong the Israelis\add* to this dayВҰ105612.
\rem /s1 An Inheritance for the Tribe of Levi
\p
\v 14 The only tribe that didn'tВҰ105618 receive an inheritance was the tribe of LeviВҰ105617 because the offeringsВҰ105621 given to Yisrael'sВҰ105624 godВҰ105623 YahwehВҰ105622 are theirВҰ105626 inheritance, just like he'd told them.\x + \xo 13:14: \xt Deu 18:1.\x*
\s1 The area assigned to Reuben's descendants
\rem /s1 The Territory Assigned to Reuben; The Land Given to the Tribe of Reuben; The Territory of Reuben
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 15 This was the land that MoshehВҰ105634 gaveВҰ105633 to the tribeВҰ105635 of ReubenВҰ105638, according to theirВҰ105639 clansВҰ105639:
\v 16 The area from AroerВҰ105644 (on the edge of the ArnonВҰ105651 riverbed) along to the townВҰ105652 in the middleВҰ105654 of the valleyВҰ105656, \add вүҲto\add* the plateauВҰ105659 \add вүҲnear\add* MedebaВҰ105662,
\v 17 Heshbon and all it's citiesВҰ105667 onВҰ105669 the plateauВҰ105669, \add includingВҰ105665\add* DibonВҰ105670, BamotВҰ105671-Baal, Beyt-Baal-Meon,
\v 18 Yahaz, KedemotВҰ105678, Mefaat,
\v 19 Kiriathaim, SibmahВҰ105682, andВҰ105681 ZeretВҰ105683-Shahar onВҰ105685 the hill \add вүҲwithin\add* the valleyВҰ105686.
\v 20 \add It also includes\add* Beyt-Peor, the slopesВҰ105690 of the PisgahВҰ105691, Beyt-Yeshimot,
\v 21 and all the citiesВҰ105696 \add вүҲonВҰ105706\add* the plateauВҰ105697, and all the kingdomВҰ105700 of Sihon (the kingВҰ105702 of the AmoritesВҰ105703 who had reignedВҰ105705 in HeshbonВҰ105706) who MoshehВҰ105709 had \add вүҲdefeatedВҰ105708\add*, he and the leadersВҰ105714 of MidianВҰ105715: EviВҰ105718 and RekemВҰ105721 and ZurВҰ105724 and HurВҰ105727 and RebaВҰ105730 (the princesВҰ105731 of Sihon who had lived in the land).
\v 22 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ105746\add* also killedВҰ105743 BalaamВҰ105738 (Beor'sВҰ105741 son who practicedВҰ105742 divinationВҰ105742) \add вүҲalong withВҰ105747 others\add*.
\v 23 The borderВҰ105753 for Reuven's descendants was the YordanВҰ105756 \add River\add*. SoВҰ105752 that was the inheritanceВҰ105759 of Reuven's descendantsвҖ”all the citiesВҰ105764 andВҰ105752 their villagesВҰ105765 allocated to their clansВҰ105763.
\s1 The area assigned to Gad's descendants
\rem /s1 The Territory Assigned to Gad; The Territory of Gad; The Land Given to the Tribe of Gad
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 24 ThisВҰ105775 was the land that MoshehВҰ105769 gaveВҰ105768 to the tribeВҰ105770 of GadВҰ105772, according to theirВҰ105776 clansВҰ105776:
\v 25 It included YazerВҰ105781 and all the citiesВҰ105784 of GileadВҰ105785 and half of the land \add вүҲwhere the AmmonitesВҰ105789 had lived\add* as far as AroerВҰ105792 \add вүҲopposite\add* RabbahВҰ105797,
\v 26 thenВҰ105799 from Heshbon to RamatВҰ105802-MizpahВҰ105803 and BetonimВҰ105804, and from MahanaimВҰ105805 to the Debir border.
\v 27 \add вүҲAlso\add* inВҰ105811 the valleyВҰ105811, Beyt-HaramВҰ105813, Beyt-Nimrah, SuccotВҰ105816, ZafonВҰ105817, and the rest of the kingdomВҰ105819 of SihonВҰ105820 (the kingВҰ105821 of HeshbonВҰ105822), withВҰ105811 the Yordan and the borderВҰ105824, as far as the endВҰ105827 of Lake Galilee, eastwardВҰ105833 beyond the Yordan \add River\add*.
\v 28 So that was the inheritanceВҰ105836 of Gad'sВҰ105839 descendantsВҰ105837вҖ”all the citiesВҰ105841 and their villagesВҰ105842 allocated to their clansВҰ105840.
\s1 The area assigned to Menashsheh's descendants
\rem /s1 The Territory of the Half-Tribe of Manasseh (East); The Territory Assigned to East Manasseh; The Land Given to the Half-Tribe of Manasseh
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 29 ThisВҰ105854 was the land that MoshehВҰ105845 gaveВҰ105844 to half of the half-tribe of MenashshehВҰ105848, accordingВҰ105855 to theirВҰ105855 clansВҰ105855:
\v 30 It went from MahanaimВҰ105859, all the Bashan, all the kingdomВҰ105865 of OgВҰ105867 (the kingВҰ105868 of the Bashan), andВҰ105871 all the towns of YairВҰ105874, whichВҰ105875 are inВҰ105876 the BashanвҖ”sixtyВҰ105877 cities.
\v 31 \add вүҲAlso\add* half of the GileadВҰ105881, plusВҰ105882 AshtarothВҰ105882 andВҰ105880 EdreiВҰ105883 (citiesВҰ105884 of the kingdomВҰ105885 of OgВҰ105886 inВҰ105887 the BashanВҰ105887). SoВҰ105880 that was for half of Machir'sВҰ105889 sons (he was one of Menashsheh's sons) allocated to theirВҰ105897 clansВҰ105897.
\p
\v 32 This was the land thatВҰ105900 MoshehВҰ105903 gaveВҰ105902 as an inheritance inВҰ105904 the plainsВҰ105904 of MoabВҰ105905 onВҰ105904 the easternВҰ105909 side of the YordanВҰ105907 \add River opposite\add* YerichoВҰ105908.
\v 33 \add вүҲHowever,\add* MoshehВҰ105917 didn'tВҰ105914 give any inheritance \add of land\add* to Levi'sВҰ105913 descendants \add because\add* Yisrael'sВҰ105921 godВҰ105920 YahwehВҰ105919 is theirВҰ105923 inheritance just as he told them.\x + \xo 13:33: \xt Num 18:20; Deu 18:2.\x*
\c 14
\s1 The division of the main block west of the Yordan
\rem /s1 The Division of the Territory West of the Jordan; The Distribution of Territory West of the Jordan; Division of the Land West of the Jordan; The Land Divided West of the Jordan; Land distributed west of Jordan
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 These are what the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* inherited in the land of CanaanВҰ105936, which EleazarВҰ105940 the priestВҰ105941 and Yehoshua (Nun'sВҰ105945 son) and the \add вүҲleaders\add* of the \add вүҲIsraelis\add* gaveВҰ105938 them as an inheritance.
\v 2 Their \add вүҲallocations were made by casting lots\add* for the nineВҰ105960 and a half tribesВҰ105961, just as YahwehВҰ105956 had commandedВҰ105955 \add вүҲthrough\add* MoshehВҰ105959.\x + \xo 14:2: \xt Num 26:52-56; 34:13.\x*
\v 3 (MoshehВҰ105968 had given the other twoВҰ105970 and a half tribesВҰ105971 theirВҰ105981 inheritance onВҰ105981 the other side of the river, butВҰ105972 the LevitesВҰ105976 weren't given land as an inheritance\x + \xo 14:3-4: \xt Num 32:33; 34:14-15; Deu 3:12-17.\x*вҖ”
\v 4 instead of land they were given citiesВҰ106002 to liveВҰ106003 in, along with the \add surrounding\add* fields for their livestockВҰ106005. Yosef'sВҰ105988 two sons MenashshehВҰ105991 and EfrayimВҰ105992 were considered as two tribesВҰ105990.)
\v 5 The \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ106017\add* did just as YahwehВҰ106010 had commandedВҰ106009 MoshehВҰ106013вҖ”theyВҰ106015 allocated blocks of the land \add as permanent possessions\add*.
\s1 Hebron is allocated to Caleb
\rem /s1 Hebron Allotted to Caleb; Caleb Requests His Land; Hebron Is Given to Caleb; Hebron Given to Caleb
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 6 \add вүҲLeaders from the tribe of\add* YehudahВҰ106027 approachedВҰ106024 Yehoshua at GilgalВҰ106031 and CalebВҰ106034 (son of YefunnehВҰ106037 the KenizziteВҰ106038) saidВҰ106032 to him, вҖңYou yourself knowВҰ106040 what YahwehВҰ106047 told the manВҰ106051 of GodВҰ106053 MoshehВҰ106050 at Kadesh-Barnea aboutВҰ106056 me and you.\x + \xo 14:6: \xt Num 14:30.\x*
\v 7 I was \add вүҲfortyВҰ106063 years old\add* when Yahweh's servantВҰ106068 MoshehВҰ106067 sentВҰ106066 me from Kadesh-Barnea to spy out the land, and I broughtВҰ106078 back \add вүҲan honest report\add*.\x + \xo 14:7: \xt Num 13:1-30.\x*
\v 8 \add вүҲThe other men\add* who wentВҰ106088 made the \add вүҲpeopleВҰ106094 terrified\add*, \add вүҲbutВҰ106086\add* I \add вүҲremained loyal to\add* my godВҰ106099 YahwehВҰ106098.
\v 9 MoshehВҰ106102 \add вүҲpromised me\add* that dayВҰ106103, saying, вҖҳThe land \add вүҲthat you walked onВҰ106113\add* will certainly be for an inheritanceВҰ106116 for you andВҰ106101 your sons \add вүҲforever\add*, because you were \add вүҲcompletely loyal to\add* my godВҰ106125 YahwehВҰ106124.вҖҷ\x + \xo 14:9: \xt Num 14:24.\x*
\v 10 Now, listen. Yahweh has kept me alive these forty-fiveВҰ106136 years since Yahweh said that to MoshehВҰ106148, \add back\add* when YisraelВҰ106152 was walking inВҰ106153 the wildernessВҰ106153. \add вүҲYes, believe itВҰ106151 or not, I'm now eighty-fiveВҰ106161.\add*
\v 11 I'm still as strongВҰ106166 today as \add I was\add* on the day that MoshehВҰ106171 sent me. \add вүҲJust like I could fight back then, I can still fight or travel just the same\add*.
\v 12 \add вүҲSo\add* now, please give me that hill countryВҰ106186 that Yahweh \add вүҲpromised\add* that day, because you yourself heardВҰ106197 \add вүҲme say\add* that the AnakimВҰ106202 lived thereВҰ106203 inВҰ106198 fortifiedВҰ106206 citiesВҰ106204. \add So now,\add* perhapsВҰ106207 Yahweh will help me to take them over just as \add *he\add* said.вҖқ
\p
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ106215\add* Yehoshua blessedВҰ106215 Yefunneh'sВҰ106224 son \add @Caleb\add* andВҰ106217 gaveВҰ106217 himВҰ106215 HebronВҰ106220 as his inheritanceВҰ106225.
\v 14 Because of that, HebronВҰ106232 belongsВҰ106230 to CalebВҰ106233 (YefunnehВҰ106236 the Kenizzite'sВҰ106237 son) as an inheritanceВҰ106238 untilВҰ106239 this dayВҰ106240, becauseВҰ106242 he was \add вүҲcompletely loyal to\add* Yisrael'sВҰ106248 godВҰ106247 YahwehВҰ106246.
\v 15 (HebronВҰ106251 used to be called KiriatВҰ106254-ArbaвҖ”\add @Arba\add* had been a \add вүҲbrave warrior\add* amongВҰ106257 the AnakimВҰ106257.)
\p ThenВҰ106250 there was a time of no more war inВҰ106257 that region.
\c 15
\s1 The area assigned to Yehudah's descendants
\rem /s1 The Territory of Judah; The Land Given to the Tribe of Judah; Allotment for Judah; The Territory Assigned to Judah
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add This was the land\add* that was assigned to Yehudah'sВҰ106268 descendantsВҰ106267 according to theirВҰ106269 clansВҰ106269:
\p It went from the ZinВҰ106276 wildernessВҰ106274 in the south to the borderВҰ106272 with EdomВҰ106273,
\v 2 andВҰ106281 their southern borderВҰ106283 was the south-facing bay at the endВҰ106285 of the \add вүҲDead Sea\add* \add (also called the Salt Sea)\add*.
\v 3 \add From there\add* it went south of the Scorpion Pass, across to ZinВҰ106301, \add вүҲclimbed\add* up to Kadesh-Barnea, crossed to HezronВҰ106307, went to AddarВҰ106309, andВҰ106294 around to KarkaВҰ106311.
\v 4 ThenВҰ106313 itВҰ106325 crosses to AzmonВҰ106314 and out to the Egyptian riverbed and \add вүҲfinishes\add* at the \add Mediterranean\add* seaВҰ106322. That will be their southernВҰ106328 borderВҰ106327.
\p
\v 5 The eastern border was the \add вүҲDead Sea\add* as far as the endВҰ106336 of the YordanВҰ106337.
\p The northernВҰ106340 border \add starts\add* at the top of the \add вүҲDead Sea\add* where the Yordan \add river\add* enters it
\v 6 thenВҰ106346 to Beyt-HoglahВҰ106349 andВҰ106346 \add further\add* northВҰ106351 to Beyt-Arabah to the Stone of BohanВҰ106357 (Reuben'sВҰ106360 son).
\v 7 ThenВҰ106362 the border went to DebirВҰ106365 from the Akor Valley, and to the northВҰ106368, turningВҰ106369 to the GilgalВҰ106372, which is in front of the AdummimВҰ106377 pass which is from the southВҰ106379 of the riverbed, thenВҰ106362 the border passedВҰ106381 over to the watersВҰ106385 of Eyn-Shemesh and itsВҰ106390 endsВҰ106390 at Eyn-RogelВҰ106394.
\v 8 \add вүҲFrom there\add* the border went up the valley of BenВҰ106398 Hinnom to the edge of the YebusiteВҰ106405 region from the southВҰ106406 (thatВҰ106415 is YerushalemВҰ106408). ThenВҰ106396 the border went to the head of the hillВҰ106414 opposite the Hinnom valley to the west, which is atВҰ106424 the endВҰ106424 of the valley of the Refa'ites to the northВҰ106428.
\v 9 \add вүҲFrom there\add* the border turned from the head of the hillВҰ106433 to the Neftoah springВҰ106436 andВҰ106430 wentВҰ106439 out to the citiesВҰ106442 of MtВҰ106433. EfronВҰ106445, thenВҰ106430 the border turned to Ba'alah (\add вүҲnow called\add* KiriatВҰ106451-Yearim).
\v 10 ThenВҰ106453 the borderВҰ106454 went around from Ba'alah to the west to Mt. SeirВҰ106460, and passed over to the shoulder of Mt. YearimВҰ106467 from the northВҰ106468 (\add вүҲalso called\add* KesalonВҰ106470), and went down to Beyt-ShemeshВҰ106474, and passed over to TimnahВҰ106476.
\v 11 \add вүҲFrom there\add* the border went out to the shoulder of EkronВҰ106483 to the northВҰ106484, then turned toward ShikkeronВҰ106487 and passedВҰ106488 over to MtВҰ106489. BaalahВҰ106491, and went out to Yabneel, then the border ended at the seaВҰ106497.
\v 12 The western border was the \add вүҲMediterranean\add* Sea. Those were the borders of \add the land given to\add* Yehudah'sВҰ106508 descendantsВҰ106506 to be allocated to theirВҰ106510 clansВҰ106510.
\s1 Caleb defeats Hebron and Debir
\rem /s1 The Land Given to Caleb; Caleb Occupies His Portion; Caleb Conquers Hebron and Debir
\s4 Promised land
\r (Jdg. 1:11-15)
\p
\v 13 YahwehВҰ106525 had instructed Yehoshua to give \add this\add* block of land to Caleb (Yefunneh'sВҰ106515 son): KiriatВҰ106529-Arba (\add вүҲnow called\add* HebronВҰ106534вҖ”Arba was Anak'sВҰ106532 fatherВҰ106531).\x + \xo 15:13-14: \xt Jdg 1:20.\x*
\v 14 CalebВҰ106538 captured \add the land\add* from Anak'sВҰ106543 threeВҰ106541 sonsВҰ106542вҖ”SheshaiВҰ106546, AhimanВҰ106549, andВҰ106536 TalmaiВҰ106552,
\v 15 thenВҰ106556 from thereВҰ106557, he \add вүҲbattled againstВҰ106558\add* DebirВҰ106561 (formerlyВҰ106565 called KiriatВҰ106568-SeferВҰ106564)
\v 16 and \add *he\add* saidВҰ106570, вҖңI'llВҰ106581 giveВҰ106581 my daughterВҰ106586 Aksah to marry \add вүҲto the man who attacksВҰ106574\add* KiriatВҰ106577-Sefer and capturesВҰ106580 it.вҖқ
\v 17 ThenВҰ106589 OthnielВҰ106590 (Kenaz'sВҰ106593 son andВҰ106596 Caleb'sВҰ106595 brotherВҰ106594) capturedВҰ106589 \add @the city\add*, \add вүҲso\add* Caleb gaveВҰ106596 his daughterВҰ106602 Aksah to him for a wife.
\v 18 ThenВҰ106605 \add вүҲwhen she married him\add*, she \add вүҲencouraged\add* him to askВҰ106608 her fatherВҰ106611 for a fieldВҰ106612, \add вүҲso\add* she got down off her donkeyВҰ106615 andВҰ106605 CalebВҰ106619 asked, вҖңWhat \add вүҲare you up to\add*?вҖқ
\v 19 вҖңGive me a blessingВҰ106628,вҖқ she answered, вҖңbecause you'veВҰ106632 givenВҰ106632 me land in the NegevВҰ106631 \add desert regionВҰ106630\add*, \add вүҲso now\add* give me some springs \add as well\add* for waterВҰ106636.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ106624\add* he gaveВҰ106637 her \add both\add* the upperВҰ106642 andВҰ106624 the lowerВҰ106645 springs.
\s1 Cities captured by Yehudah's descendants
\rem /s1 The Towns Judah Inherited; The Cities of Judah; The Towns of Judah
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 20 This is Yehudah'sВҰ106653 inheritanceВҰ106649 according to theirВҰ106654 clansВҰ106654:
\v 21 The citiesВҰ106657 atВҰ106667 the edge of Yehudah'sВҰ106662 block toward the borderВҰ106665 withВҰ106667 EdomВҰ106666 inВҰ106667 Negev were KabzeelВҰ106668, EderВҰ106669, Yagur,
\v 22 KinahВҰ106672, DimonahВҰ106673, AdadahВҰ106674,
\v 23 Kedesh, Hatsor, IthnanВҰ106678,
\v 24 Zif, TelemВҰ106681, BealotВҰ106682,
\v 25 Hatsor-Hadattah, KeriotВҰ106687-HezronВҰ106688 (\add вүҲalso called\add* Hatsor),
\v 26 Amam, ShemaВҰ106693, Molodah,
\v 27 HazarВҰ106696-Gaddah, HeshmonВҰ106698, Beyt-Pelet,
\v 28 HazarВҰ106702-Shual, Be'er-Sheva, andВҰ106702 BiziothiahВҰ106706,
\v 29 BaalahВҰ106708, IyimВҰ106709, EtsemВҰ106710,
\v 30 EltoladВҰ106712, KesilВҰ106713, HormahВҰ106714,
\v 31 ZiklagВҰ106716, MadmannahВҰ106717, SansannahВҰ106718,
\v 32 LebaotВҰ106720, ShilhimВҰ106721, AinВҰ106722, andВҰ106720 RimmonВҰ106723вҖ”\add вүҲa totalВҰ106724 of\add* twenty-nineВҰ106727 citiesВҰ106726 as well as theirВҰ106729 villagesВҰ106729.
\p
\v 33 \add ThenВҰ106732 down\add* inВҰ106732 the lowlandsВҰ106732 were EshtaolВҰ106733, ZorahВҰ106734, AshnahВҰ106735,
\v 34 ZanoahВҰ106737, Eyn-Gannim, TappuahВҰ106740, Enam,
\v 35 Yarmut, AdullamВҰ106744, Sokoh, AzekahВҰ106746,
\v 36 ShaaraimВҰ106748, AdithaimВҰ106749, andВҰ106748 GederahВҰ106750 (\add also called\add* GederothaimВҰ106751)вҖ”\add вүҲa total of\add* fourteen citiesВҰ106752 as well as theirВҰ106756 \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ106756.
\p
\v 37 \add Also\add* ZenanВҰ106758, HadashahВҰ106759, MigdalВҰ106760-GadВҰ106762,
\v 38 DileanВҰ106764, MizpahВҰ106765, YoktheelВҰ106766,
\v 39 Lachish, BozkatВҰ106769, EglonВҰ106770,
\v 40 Kabbon, LahmasВҰ106773, KitlishВҰ106774,
\v 41 GederotВҰ106776, BeytВҰ106777-DagonВҰ106779, NaamahВҰ106780, andВҰ106776 MakkedahВҰ106781вҖ”sixteen citiesВҰ106782 as well as theirВҰ106786 villagesВҰ106786.
\p
\v 42 \add Also\add* LibnahВҰ106789, EtherВҰ106790, AshanВҰ106791,
\v 43 YiftahВҰ106793, AshnahВҰ106794, NezibВҰ106795,
\v 44 KeilahВҰ106797, AkzibВҰ106798, andВҰ106797 MareshaВҰ106799вҖ”nineВҰ106801 citiesВҰ106800 as well as theirВҰ106802 villagesВҰ106802.
\p
\v 45 \add Also\add* Ekron with its townsВҰ106805 and villagesВҰ106806
\v 46 from Ekron to the \add вүҲMediterranean\add*вҖ”\add вүҲthose near\add* AshdodВҰ106816 and theirВҰ106817 villagesВҰ106817.
\p
\v 47 \add Also\add* Ashdod and its towns and its villages, GazaВҰ106822 and its towns and its villages, as far as the riverbed of EgyptВҰ106828 and the \add вүҲMediterranean\add* seaВҰ106829 and the border.
\p
\v 48 \add Also\add* inВҰ106835 the hill countryВҰ106835: ShamirВҰ106836, YattirВҰ106837, SocohВҰ106838,
\v 49 DannahВҰ106840, Kiriat-Sannah (\add вүҲalso called\add* DebirВҰ106845),
\v 50 Anab, EshtemohВҰ106848, Anim,
\v 51 GoshenВҰ106851, HolonВҰ106852, andВҰ106851 GilohВҰ106853вҖ”eleven citiesВҰ106854 as well as theirВҰ106858 villagesВҰ106858.
\p
\v 52 \add Also\add* Arab, DumahВҰ106861, EshanВҰ106862,
\v 53 YanimВҰ106864, Beyt-Tappuah, Afekah,
\v 54 HumtahВҰ106871, and Kiriat-Arba (\add вүҲalso called\add* HebronВҰ106875) and ZiorвҖ”nineВҰ106878 citiesВҰ106877 as well as theirВҰ106879 villagesВҰ106879.
\p
\v 55 \add Also\add* MaonВҰ106882, KarmelВҰ106884, ZifВҰ106885, Yuttah,
\v 56 Yezreel, YokdeamВҰ106889, ZanoahВҰ106890,
\v 57 Kayin, GibeahВҰ106893, and TimnahВҰ106894вҖ”tenВҰ106896 citiesВҰ106895 as well as theirВҰ106897 villagesВҰ106897.
\p
\v 58 \add Also\add* HalhulВҰ106899, Beyt-ZurВҰ106902, GedorВҰ106903,
\v 59 MaaratВҰ106905, Beyt-Anot, andВҰ106905 EltekonВҰ106909вҖ”sixВҰ106911 citiesВҰ106910 as well as theirВҰ106912 villagesВҰ106912.
\p
\v 60 \add Also\add* Kiriat-BaalВҰ106916 (\add вүҲalso called\add* Kiriat-YearimВҰ106919) and RabbahВҰ106920вҖ”twoВҰ106922 citiesВҰ106921 as well as theirВҰ106923 villagesВҰ106923.
\p
\v 61 In the wildernessВҰ106926, Beyt-ArabahВҰ106928, MiddinВҰ106929, SecacahВҰ106930,
\v 62 NibshanВҰ106932, the City of Salt, andВҰ106932 Eyn-GediвҖ”sixВҰ106939 citiesВҰ106938 as well as theirВҰ106940 villagesВҰ106940.
\p
\v 63 \add вүҲButВҰ106942\add* Yehudah'sВҰ106953 descendants weren't able to defeat the YebusitesВҰ106944 who lived inВҰ106961 YerushalemВҰ106946, so \add *they\add* have lived among the tribe of Yehudah to this dayВҰ106963.\x + \xo 15:63: \xt Jdg 1:21; 2Sam 5:6; 1Ch 11:4.\x*
\c 16
\s1 The allocation to Yosef's descendants
\rem /s1 Allotment for Ephraim and Manasseh; The Inheritance of Ephraim and West Manasseh; The Territory Assigned to Ephraim and West Manasseh; The Territory of Ephraim
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 The block for Yosef'sВҰ106970 descendantsВҰ106969\f + \fr 16:1 \ft i.e., the half-tribes of Efrayim and Menashsheh.\f* wentВҰ106967 from the YordanВҰ106971 atВҰ106979 YerichoВҰ106974 (east of the \add вүҲsprings\add*), through the wildernessВҰ106976 into the hill countryВҰ106979 of Beyt-El.
\v 2 It wentВҰ106984 out from Beyt-El to LuzВҰ106988 thenВҰ106984 alongВҰ106989 the borderВҰ106992 with the ArkitesВҰ106993 at AtarotВҰ106994.
\v 3 ThenВҰ106996 itВҰ107013 went west to the border with the Yafletites as far as the border with Lower Beyt-HoronВҰ107007 andВҰ106996 as far as GezerВҰ107011, thenВҰ106996 out to the \add вүҲMediterranean\add*.
\rem /s1 The Land Given to Ephraim
\p
\v 4 \add вүҲSoВҰ107017\add* Yosef'sВҰ107020 sons MenashshehВҰ107021 andВҰ107022 EfrayimВҰ107022 receivedВҰ107017 an inheritanceВҰ107017.
\s1 The allocation to Efrayim's descendants
\rem /s1 Ephraim
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 5 The allotment for Efrayim'sВҰ107028 descendantsВҰ107026 according to their clansВҰ107029 was at AtarotВҰ107034-AddarВҰ107035 in the east, going as far as Upper Beyt-HoronВҰ107039
\v 6 andВҰ107042 out to the \add вүҲMediterranean\add*. From Mikmetat in the northВҰ107046, the border wentВҰ107042 eastwardВҰ107049 toward TaanatВҰ107050-ShilohВҰ107051 thenВҰ107042 further east to YanoahВҰ107055.
\v 7 From YanoahВҰ107058 it wentВҰ107057 to AtarotВҰ107059 andВҰ107057 NaarahВҰ107060, reached YerichoВҰ107062 thenВҰ107057 cameВҰ107063 out atВҰ107062 the YordanВҰ107064.
\v 8 \add The northern borderВҰ107068 went\add* from Tappuah to the KanahВҰ107071 riverbed andВҰ107072 then out to the \add вүҲMediterranean\add*. That was the inheritanceВҰ107076 of Efrayim'sВҰ107080 descendantsВҰ107078 according to theirВҰ107081 clansВҰ107081,
\v 9 \add вүҲalthough\add* some of the cities with theirВҰ107095 villagesВҰ107095 for Efrayim'sВҰ107086 descendants were \add actually\add* inside the territory assigned to Menashsheh'sВҰ107091 descendants.
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ107097\add* they didn'tВҰ107097 \add вүҲcapture the land of\add* the CanaanitesВҰ107101 who lived inВҰ107103 GezerВҰ107103, so they've lived within EfrayimВҰ107107 to this dayВҰ107110 andВҰ107097 were forcedВҰ107113 to serve as labourersВҰ107113.\x + \xo 16:10: \xt Jdg 1:29.\x*
\c 17
\s1 The allocation to Menashsheh's descendants
\rem /s1 The Land Given to West Manasseh; West Manasseh; The Other Half-Tribe of Manasseh (West)
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 The allotment for Menashsheh'sВҰ107121 descendants (Yosef'sВҰ107126 eldest son) \add included a special allotment for\add* (Gilead'sВҰ107131 fatherВҰ107130) MakirВҰ107127вҖ”he was given Gilead and BashanВҰ107141 because he was a \add вүҲpowerful warrior\add*.
\v 2 The other Menashsheh clans \add that were allocated land\add* were the AbiezerВҰ107149, HelekВҰ107152, AsrielВҰ107154, ShekemВҰ107157, HeferВҰ107160, andВҰ107143 ShemidaВҰ107162 clans. (They were the sons of Yosef's son Menashsheh \add who led their own\add* clans.)
\v 3 \add вүҲButВҰ107172\add* Zelofehad (son of HeferВҰ107175, son of GileadВҰ107178, son of MakirВҰ107181, son of MenashshehВҰ107184) had no sonsвҖ”only daughters who were named MahlahВҰ107197, NoahВҰ107198, HoglahВҰ107199, Milkah, andВҰ107172 TirzahВҰ107201.
\v 4 They approached the priestВҰ107206 Eleazar and Yehoshua and the other leadersВҰ107214 and said, вҖңYahweh toldВҰ107217 MoshehВҰ107220 to give us an inheritance along with our brothers.вҖқ \add вүҲSoВҰ107203\add* he\f + \fr 17:4 \ft It's not clear who this вҖҳheвҖҷ refers to hereвҖ”some translations choose Eleazar (implied by the sentence structure) and others choose Yehoshua (implied by past allocations of land).\f* gave them an inheritance (like he'd given theirВҰ107236 uncles), as Yahweh \add вүҲhad instructedВҰ107217 them\add*.\x + \xo 17:4: \xt Num 27:1-7.\x*
\v 5 \add вүҲSoВҰ107238\add* tenВҰ107242 blocks were allocated to MenashshehВҰ107241 \add tribe\add* as well as GileadВҰ107245 andВҰ107238 BashanВҰ107246 whichВҰ107247 were across the YordanВҰ107249
\v 6 because Menashsheh's daughtersВҰ107252 received inheritancesВҰ107254 along with his sons. The land of GileadВҰ107259 belongedВҰ107260 to the rest of Menashsheh's sons.
\p
\v 7 The borderВҰ107267 for MenashshehВҰ107269 went from AsherВҰ107270 to Mikmetat \add вүҲopposite\add* ShekemВҰ107276, thenВҰ107266 went \add вүҲsouthВҰ107281\add* towards the spring at Tappuah.
\v 8 (The Tappuah \em land\em* was for MenashshehВҰ107296, butВҰ107292 Tappuah \add town\add* was for EfrayimВҰ107298.)
\v 9 ThenВҰ107300 the border went southВҰ107304 to the KanahВҰ107303 riverbedвҖ”the cities there belongedВҰ107308 to EfrayimВҰ107308 even though they were inside Menashsheh'sВҰ107311 landвҖ”thenВҰ107300 the border stayed on the northВҰ107314 side of the riverbed andВҰ107300 extended to the \add вүҲMediterraneanВҰ107313\add*.
\v 10 \add So\add* the south was for EfrayimВҰ107321 and the north was for MenashshehВҰ107323, and the seaВҰ107325 was the \add western\add* borderВҰ107326, meeting AsherВҰ107327 from the north and Yissakar from the east.
\v 11 MenashshehВҰ107334 was allocated cities inside \add both\add* Yissakar's and Asher'sВҰ107336 territories: Beyt-Shan, IbleamВҰ107341, DorВҰ107346, EndorВҰ107351, TaanachВҰ107354, and MegiddoВҰ107357 along withВҰ107335 their \add вүҲsurrounding towns\add*.\f + \fr 17:11 \ft We've omitted the final Hebrew phrase here (the three of Nafet) since it's unclear what it means (plus it's not considered to be a vital point in the narrative).\f*
\v 12 \add вүҲButВҰ107362\add* Menashsheh'sВҰ107365 descendantsВҰ107364 weren't able to takeВҰ107366 possessionВҰ107366 of those citiesВҰ107369, \add вүҲso\add* the CanaanitesВҰ107372 continued to liveВҰ107373 in the region.\x + \xo 17:12-13: \xt Jdg 1:27-28.\x*
\v 13 \add вүҲWhenВҰ107377 the IsraelisВҰ107381 strengthened their position\add*, they were able to forceВҰ107386 those CanaanitesВҰ107385 to work for them, \add вүҲbutВҰ107377\add* they weren't able to \add вүҲdrive them out\add*.
\s1 Efrayim and Menashsheh's descendants are given additional land
\rem /s1 The Tribe of Joseph Protests; Ephraim and West Manasseh Request More Land
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 14 Then the \add two\add* \add вүҲhalf-tribes of Efrayim and Menashsheh\add* asked Yehoshua, вҖңWhy have youВҰ107400 \add only\add* givenВҰ107400 to \add #us\add* one measured allocation as an inheritanceВҰ107402 when \add #we're\add* \add very\add* numerousВҰ107410 \add because\add* YahwehВҰ107418 has \add вүҲalready\add* blessedВҰ107417 \add #us\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖңIf \add вүҲthere's so many of you\add*,вҖқ Yehoshua \add вүҲanswered\add*, вҖңand if Efrayim'sВҰ107444 hill-country is too small for you, goВҰ107429 into the forestedВҰ107431 area of the PerizzitesВҰ107436 and the RefaitesВҰ107437 and clearВҰ107432 some land for yourselves there.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖңThe hill countryВҰ107453 \add certainly\add* isn'tВҰ107449 big enough for \add all of\add* us,вҖқ \add *they\add* respondedВҰ107446, вҖңplusВҰ107454 the CanaanitesВҰ107458 living in the YezreelВҰ107470 valley and in Beyt-Shan and the surrounding towns have iron chariotsВҰ107454.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 \add вүҲSoВҰ107472\add* Yehoshua told the \add вүҲhalf-tribes of EfrayimВҰ107478 and MenashshehВҰ107479\add*, вҖң\add Yes\add*, there's a lot of you and you're very powerfulВҰ107485. One land allotment \add вүҲwouldn't be enough for you\add*
\v 18 \add вүҲso\add* the hill countryВҰ107496 will be yoursВҰ107506 \add as well\add*. \add вүҲHowever\add*, it's a forestВҰ107502 and you'll have to clearВҰ107504 it to the bordersВҰ107507. You'll \add need to\add* drive out the CanaanitesВҰ107513 even if they are strongВҰ107519 and with iron chariotsВҰ107515.вҖқ
\c 18
\s1 Allocations for the remaining seven tribes
\rem /s1 The Territories of the Remaining Tribes; Division of the Rest of the Land; The Allotments of the Remaining Land; The Division of the Rest of the Land
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Then all the IsraelisВҰ107529 assembledВҰ107523 at ShilohВҰ107530 and set up the sacredВҰ107535 tentВҰ107535 thereВҰ107532. The \add вүҲbattles over the land had stopped\add*
\v 2 butВҰ107541 sevenВҰ107551 of \add *their\add* tribesВҰ107552 hadn't had their inheritancesВҰ107550 assigned \add yet\add*.
\v 3 Yehoshua asked the IsraelisВҰ107559, вҖң\add вүҲHow much longer are you all goingВҰ107565 to put off capturing\add* the land thatВҰ107570 your ancestors' GodВҰ107574 YahwehВҰ107573 has givenВҰ107571 you?
\v 4 Choose threeВҰ107579 menВҰ107580 from each \add of those seven\add*\f + \fr 18:4 \ft Not in the Hebrew but implied by verse 5 as they go on to divide the surveyed land into seven portions.\f* tribesВҰ107581 and I'll sendВҰ107582 them out to \add вүҲscout around\add* \add and inspect\add* the land and writeВҰ107586 \add вүҲdescriptionsВҰ107586 of it in terms of potential allocations and bring it\add* to me.
\v 5 They can divideВҰ107593 \add @that land\add* into sevenВҰ107595 parts. (YehudahВҰ107597 will maintain theirВҰ107608 territory in the southВҰ107602, andВҰ107603 Yosef'sВҰ107604 tribes in the northВҰ107609.)
\v 6 You all should write descriptionsВҰ107612 of the seven parts and bringВҰ107618 them here to me, and in frontВҰ107625 of our godВҰ107627 YahwehВҰ107626, I'llВҰ107621 throwВҰ107621 dice for you \add to allocate them to the seven tribes\add*.
\v 7 However, the LevitesВҰ107633 don'tВҰ107630 receive a portionВҰ107632, because their inheritance is Yahweh's priesthoodВҰ107637. GadВҰ107640 and Reuven and the MenashshehВҰ107644 half-tribe have \add already\add* receivedВҰ107645 their inheritance thatВҰ107650 Yahweh's servantВҰ107654 MoshehВҰ107653 allocated to them onВҰ107634 the easternВҰ107649 side of the YordanВҰ107648.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ107657\add* the \add chosen\add* menВҰ107658 \add вүҲgot ready to leave\add* and Yehoshua instructedВҰ107660 them, вҖңGo and walkВҰ107671 around that land and writeВҰ107673 \add a report\add* and \add вүҲbring it back\add* to me. ThenВҰ107657 I'llВҰ107678 throwВҰ107678 dice for you all \add вүҲin frontВҰ107681\add* of YahwehВҰ107682 here in ShilohВҰ107683.вҖқ
\v 9 ThenВҰ107685 the menВҰ107686 left andВҰ107685 \add вүҲwalked through the area\add*, writingВҰ107689 down \add their recommendations\add* for dividing the sevenВҰ107691 portionsВҰ107692 according to the citiesВҰ107690 \add in the area\add*, thenВҰ107685 theyВҰ107696 returned back to YehoshuaВҰ107699 at the campВҰ107702 at ShilohВҰ107703.
\v 10 \add вүҲSoВҰ107705\add* Yehoshua threwВҰ107705 dice for them at ShilohВҰ107709 \add вүҲin frontВҰ107710\add* of YahwehВҰ107711, andВҰ107705 \add вүҲso that land was allocated to those remaining seven tribes\add*.
\s1 The allocation to Benyamin's descendants
\rem /s1 The Land Given to Benjamin; The Territory of Benjamin; Allotment for Benjamin; The Territory Assigned to Benjamin
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 11 The tribeВҰ107726 of BenyaminВҰ107729 won the \add first\add* draw and the area for their clansВҰ107730 was between the land assigned to YehudahВҰ107736 and that assigned to \add вүҲEfrayim and Menashsheh\add*.
\v 12 Their northern borderВҰ107743 went from the YordanВҰ107748 thenВҰ107741 to the northern side of YerichoВҰ107754 andВҰ107741 up into the hill countryВҰ107757 to the west, comingВҰ107759 out inВҰ107757 the wildernessВҰ107762 atВҰ107757 Beyt-Aven.
\v 13 ThenВҰ107766 it wentВҰ107779 across towards LuzВҰ107769 (\add вүҲnow called\add* Beyt-El) to the southern edge thenВҰ107766 downhill towards AtarotВҰ107781-AddarВҰ107782 beside the hillВҰ107785 south of lowerВҰ107791 Beyt-Horon.
\v 14 ThenВҰ107793 the western borderВҰ107794 turned from thatВҰ107803 hillВҰ107802 andВҰ107793 wentВҰ107811 southВҰ107810, coming out at Kiriat-BaalВҰ107818 (\add вүҲalso called\add* Kiriat-YearimВҰ107821вҖ”a townВҰ107822 belonging to YehudahВҰ107824) thus forming the western side.
\v 15 The southernВҰ107832 borderВҰ107837 wentВҰ107839 west from KiriatВҰ107835-Yearim to the springВҰ107842 at Neftoah,
\v 16 then downhill to the BenВҰ107856-Hinnon valley (inВҰ107861 the valley of the RefaitesВҰ107862 to the northВҰ107863) then downhill to Hinnon valley to the edge of the YebusitesВҰ107870 andВҰ107846 downhill to Eyn-RogelВҰ107874.
\v 17 ThenВҰ107876 it turned northwardВҰ107877 and wentВҰ107878 \add west\add* to Eyn-ShemeshВҰ107880 and across to GelilotВҰ107884 oppositeВҰ107887 the AdummimВҰ107889 pass, before going downhill to the Stone of BohanВҰ107892 (Reuben'sВҰ107895 son).
\v 18 It extended over to the northernВҰ107904 slopeВҰ107900 of the Yordan valley andВҰ107905 thenВҰ107897 downhill into the \add actual\add* valley.
\v 19 \add *It\add* thenВҰ107908 wentВҰ107917 \add east\add* to the northern slopeВҰ107912 of Beyt-HoglahВҰ107915 before coming out at the \add вүҲnorth endВҰ107932\add* of the \add вүҲDead Sea\add* \add (also called the Salt Sea)\add* where the YordanВҰ107933 river flows into itВҰ107908. That was the southern boundaryВҰ107922
\v 20 andВҰ107939 the YordanВҰ107939 borders it on the east. Those were the borders of Benyamin'sВҰ107949 descendants' inheritanceВҰ107947 accordingВҰ107950 to theirВҰ107952 clansВҰ107952.
\rem /s1 The Towns Given to Benjamin
\p
\v 21 The citiesВҰ107955 allocated to Benyamin'sВҰ107958 descendantsВҰ107957 andВҰ107954 theirВҰ107959 clansВҰ107959 were: YerichoВҰ107960, Beyt-Hoglah, Emek-Keziz,
\v 22 Beyt-Arabah, ZemaraimВҰ107969, Beyt-El,
\v 23 AvvimВҰ107974, ParahВҰ107975, OfrahВҰ107976,
\v 24 Kefar-AmmoniВҰ107978, Ofni, andВҰ107978 GebaВҰ107982вҖ”a total of twelve citiesВҰ107983 as well as theirВҰ107987 \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ107987.
\v 25 \add Also\add* Gibeon, RamahВҰ107990, BeerotВҰ107991,
\v 26 Mizpah, KefirahВҰ107994, MozahВҰ107995,
\v 27 RekemВҰ107997, IrpeelВҰ107998, TaralahВҰ107999,
\v 28 Zelah, HaelefВҰ108002, YebusВҰ108003 (\add вүҲnow called\add* YerushalemВҰ108006), GibeahВҰ108007, andВҰ108001 KiriatВҰ108008вҖ”\add a total of\add* fourteen citiesВҰ108009 as well as their \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108013. Those were Benyamin'sВҰ108018 descendants' inheritanceВҰ108015 according to their clansВҰ108019.
\c 19
\s1 The allocation to Shimeon's descendants
\rem /s1 The Territory Assigned to Simeon; The Land Given to Simeon; The Territory of Simeon; Allotment for Simeon
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 The secondВҰ108024 draw wentВҰ108022 to Shimeon's (Simeon'sВҰ108025) descendants and the land for their clansВҰ108030 was in the middleВҰ108033 of Yehudah'sВҰ108037 territory.
\v 2 Shimeon's inheritanceВҰ108041 \add вүҲincluded\add*: BeerВҰ108042-Sheba,\f + \fr 19:2 \ft TC: Ancient manuscripts differ, with some adding Sheba (possibly a mistaken reduplication) or Shema here (but that would make the total number wrong that's given in v6).\f* MoladahВҰ108046,\x + \xo 19:2-8: \xt 1Ch 4:28-33.\x*
\v 3 HazarshualВҰ108048, BalahВҰ108050, EzemВҰ108051,
\v 4 Eltolad, BetulВҰ108054, HormahВҰ108055,
\v 5 ZiklagВҰ108057, Beyt-Markabot. Hatsarsusah,
\v 6 Beyt-Lebaot, andВҰ108064 SharuhenВҰ108066вҖ”thirteen citiesВҰ108067 as well as theirВҰ108071 \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108071.
\p
\v 7 \add Also\add* Ain, RimmonВҰ108075, EterВҰ108076, and AshaвҖ”fourВҰ108079 citiesВҰ108078 as well as theirВҰ108080 \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108080,
\v 8 andВҰ108082 all the \add further\add* villagesВҰ108084 aroundВҰ108086 those citiesВҰ108087 as far as Baalat-BeerВҰ108092 (\add also called\add* RamahВҰ108093 of the NegevВҰ108094). That was Shimeon's descendants' inheritanceВҰ108096 according to theirВҰ108101 clansВҰ108101.
\v 9 This \add took away\add* some of Yehudah's inheritance andВҰ108118 gave itВҰ108111 to Shimeons descendants because Yehudah's \add initial\add* area was more than \add вүҲtheyВҰ108118 needed\add*.
\s1 The allocation to Zebulun's descendants
\rem /s1 The Land Given to Zebulun; The Territory of Zebulun; Allotment for Zebulun; The Territory Assigned to Zebulun
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 10 The thirdВҰ108128 draw went to Zebulun'sВҰ108130 descendantsВҰ108129 according to their clansВҰ108131. The \add southern\add* borderВҰ108133 for their inheritanceВҰ108134 \add вүҲstarted\add* at SaridВҰ108137
\v 11 and went \add west\add* to MaralahВҰ108143 and DabbeshetВҰ108145 thenВҰ108139 to the riverbed facing YokneamВҰ108154.
\v 12 \add Also\add* from SaridВҰ108157 it went toward the east beside the borderВҰ108163 with KislotВҰ108165-Tabor and then on to DaberatВҰ108169 and then to YafiaВҰ108171.
\v 13 From thereВҰ108173 itВҰ108174 extended east to Gittah-HeferВҰ108178 and Ittah-Katsin and \add north\add* to RimmonВҰ108182 before turning to Neah.
\v 14 ThenВҰ108186 \add *it\add* passed northВҰ108189 of HannatonВҰ108190 ending at YiftahВҰ108194-ElВҰ108196 valleyВҰ108193.
\v 15 \add It included the cities of\add* KattatВҰ108198, NahalalВҰ108199, ShimronВҰ108200, IdalahВҰ108201, andВҰ108198 BethlehemвҖ”\add a total of\add* twelve cities as well as theirВҰ108208 \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108208.
\v 16 That was Zebulun'sВҰ108214 descendants' inheritanceВҰ108211 accordingВҰ108215 to their clansВҰ108215, \add includingВҰ108218\add* those citiesВҰ108216 as well as their \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108218.
\s1 The allocation to Yissakar's descendants
\rem /s1 The Territory Assigned to Issachar; Allotment for Issachar; The Territory of Issachar; The Land Given to Issachar
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 17 The fourthВҰ108224 draw wentВҰ108222 to Yissakar's descendantsВҰ108225 accordingВҰ108227 to theirВҰ108227 clansВҰ108227.
\v 18 \add вүҲTheir land\add* \add included the cities of\add* YezreelВҰ108231, KesulotВҰ108232, ShunemВҰ108233,
\v 19 Hafaraim, ShionВҰ108236, AnaharatВҰ108237,
\v 20 RabbitВҰ108239, KishionВҰ108240, EbetsВҰ108241,
\v 21 RemetВҰ108243, Eyn-Gannim, Eyn-Haddah, andВҰ108243 Beyt-Pazzets.
\v 22 The borderВҰ108253 \add of their allotment\add* met withВҰ108254 TaborВҰ108254, ShahazumahВҰ108255, andВҰ108252 Beyt-Shemesh, coming out \add inВҰ108254 the east\add* atВҰ108254 the YordanВҰ108262вҖ”\add a total of\add* sixteen citiesВҰ108263 as well as their \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108267.
\v 23 That was Yissakar's descendants' inheritanceВҰ108270 according to their clansВҰ108275, \add includingВҰ108277\add* those citiesВҰ108276 as well as their \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108277.
\s1 The allocation to Asher's descendants
\rem /s1 The Territory of Asher; Allotment for Asher; The Land Given to Asher; The Territory Assigned to Asher
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 24 The fifthВҰ108282 draw wentВҰ108280 to Asher'sВҰ108286 descendantsВҰ108284 accordingВҰ108287 to theirВҰ108287 clansВҰ108287.
\v 25 \add вүҲTheir land\add* \add included the cities of\add* HelkatВҰ108291, HaliВҰ108292, BetenВҰ108293, Akshaf,
\v 26 AllammelekВҰ108296, Amad, and MishalВҰ108298. Their \add western\add* \add @border\add* started atВҰ108300 Mt. KarmelВҰ108300 and ShihorlibnatВҰ108302
\v 27 and turnedВҰ108305 back to the east to Beyt-DagonВҰ108309 and the border withВҰ108311 ZebulunВҰ108311 and the Yiftah-El valley to the north. ThenВҰ108305 it went to Beyt-Emek and NeielВҰ108319 and north to Kabul,
\v 28 Abdon, RehobВҰ108327, HammonВҰ108328 andВҰ108326 KanahВҰ108329, as far as Greater SidonВҰ108331.
\v 29 The borderВҰ108344 thenВҰ108334 turned back to RamahВҰ108336 and to the fortifiedВҰ108340 cityВҰ108339 of Tsor \add (commonly known as TyreВҰ108342)\add* and turns \add вүҲwest\add* to HosahВҰ108345 coming out at the \add @Mediterranean\add* near AkzibВҰ108351.
\v 30 \add It also included\add* UmmahВҰ108353, AfekВҰ108354, andВҰ108353 RehobВҰ108355вҖ”\add a total of\add* twenty-twoВҰ108357 citiesВҰ108356 as well as theirВҰ108359 \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108359.
\v 31 That was Asher'sВҰ108366 descendants' inheritanceВҰ108362 according to their clansВҰ108367, \add includingВҰ108370\add* those citiesВҰ108368 as well as their \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108370.
\s1 The allocation to Naftali's descendants
\rem /s1 Allotment for Naphtali; The Territory Assigned to Naphtali; The Territory of Naphtali; The Land Given to Naphtali
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 32 TheВҰ108379 sixthВҰ108377 draw wentВҰ108375 to Naftali'sВҰ108374 descendants according to theirВҰ108380 clansВҰ108380.
\v 33 Their borderВҰ108383 started inВҰ108386 Helef (where there was an oak treeВҰ108385 at ZaanannimВҰ108386) thenВҰ108382 Adami-Nekeb and Yabneel and onВҰ108386 to LakkumВҰ108392 before exiting at the YordanВҰ108395.
\v 34 ThenВҰ108397 \add *it\add* turned west to AznotВҰ108400-TaborВҰ108401 and from thereВҰ108403 to HukkokВҰ108404, meeting \add the border\add* with ZebulunВҰ108406 on the southВҰ108407, \add the border\add* with AsherВҰ108408 on the west, and \add the border\add* with YehudahВҰ108411 on the east.
\v 35 The fortifiedВҰ108417 citiesВҰ108416 were Tsiddim, Tser, HammatВҰ108420, RakkatВҰ108421, KinneretВҰ108422,
\v 36 Adamah, RamahВҰ108425, Hatsor,
\v 37 Kedesh, EdreiВҰ108429, Eyn-Hatsor,
\v 38 YironВҰ108433, MigdalВҰ108434-El, HoremВҰ108437, Beyt-Anat, andВҰ108433 Beyt-ShemeshвҖ”\add a total of\add* nineteen citiesВҰ108443 as well as theirВҰ108447 \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108447.
\v 39 That was Naftali'sВҰ108454 descendants' inheritanceВҰ108450 according to their clansВҰ108455, \add includingВҰ108457\add* those citiesВҰ108456 as well as their \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108457.
\s1 The allocation to Dan's descendants
\rem /s1 The Land Given to Dan; Allotment for Dan; The Territory of Dan; The Territory Assigned to Dan
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 40 The \add final\add* seventhВҰ108467 draw wentВҰ108465 to Dan'sВҰ108463 descendantsВҰ108461 according to theirВҰ108464 clansВҰ108464.
\v 41 \add вүҲTheir land\add* \add included the cities of\add* TsorahВҰ108472, EshtaolВҰ108473, Ir-ShemeshВҰ108474,
\v 42 ShaalabbinВҰ108477, Ayyalon, andВҰ108477 Yitlah,
\v 43 Elon, TimnahВҰ108482, EkronВҰ108483,
\v 44 EltekehВҰ108485, GibbetonВҰ108486, BaalatВҰ108487,
\v 45 Yehud, Bene-Berak, Gat-Rimmon,
\v 46 Meyarkon, RakkonВҰ108499, andВҰ108499 the area oppositeВҰ108503 Yafo \add (JoppaВҰ108504)\add*.
\v 47 Dan's borderВҰ108526 went out from them.\f + \fr 19:47 \ft Translations vary widely here because we're not sure what is meant by the literal rendering that we've kept here.\f* ThenВҰ108506 Dan's descendants battled against Leshem and capturedВҰ108521 it and \add вүҲslaughtered their inhabitants\add*. \add вүҲSoВҰ108506\add* they took it over and settled inВҰ108532 Leshem \add вүҲbutВҰ108506\add* they renamed it to вҖҳDanвҖҷ after their ancestorВҰ108538.\x + \xo 19:47: \xt Jdg 18:27-29.\x*
\v 48 That was Dan'sВҰ108545 descendants' inheritanceВҰ108541 according to their clansВҰ108546, \add includingВҰ108549\add* those citiesВҰ108547 as well as their \add surrounding\add* villagesВҰ108549.
\s1 Yehoshua's allocation
\rem /s1 The Land Given to Joshua; The Final Assignment of the Land; Allotment for Joshua; Joshua's Inheritance
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 49 \add вүҲAfter the allocation of the blocks of land to the various tribes\add*, the \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ108562\add* gaveВҰ108559 Yehoshua (Nun'sВҰ108567 son) his \add ownВҰ108553\add* inheritanceВҰ108563 amongВҰ108568 them.
\p
\v 50 \add вүҲFollowing Yahweh's instructions to give Yehoshua whatever\add* city he askedВҰ108580 for, he was given TimnatВҰ108583-SerahВҰ108585 in the hill countryВҰ108586 of EfrayimВҰ108587 and he builtВҰ108588 \add up\add* thatВҰ108579 city and lived in it.
\p
\v 51 Those were the allotments thatВҰ108597 EleazarВҰ108599 the priestВҰ108600 and Yehoshua (Nun'sВҰ108605 son) gaveВҰ108598 to the \add вүҲleaders\add* of the IsraeliВҰ108611 tribesВҰ108608 as their inheritancesВҰ108596. It was done by throwing dice there in ShilohВҰ108615 in frontВҰ108616 of YahwehВҰ108617 atВҰ108613 the opening of the sacredВҰ108619 tentВҰ108619, and so the land division was completed.
\c 20
\s1 The refuge cities
\rem /s1 Cities of Refuge; Cities of refuge; The Cities of Refuge
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehВҰ108629 told Yehoshua,\x + \xo 20:1-9: \xt Num 35:9-34; Deu 4:41-43; 19:1-13.\x*
\v 2 вҖңTell the IsraelisВҰ108639 to select some citiesВҰ108645 thatВҰ108647 peopleВҰ108638 can flee to inВҰ108651 order to be safe, just as I instructed you through MoshehВҰ108653,
\v 3 so that if \add вүҲsomeone accidentallyВҰ108661 kills someone else\add*, theyВҰ108665 can escape thereВҰ108656 andВҰ108665 be safe \add вүҲfrom the dead person'sВҰ108660 family\add*.
\v 4 WhenВҰ108671 \add @that person\add* flees to one of theseВҰ108677 citiesВҰ108676, \add they mustВҰ108671\add* standВҰ108678 atВҰ108683 the city gate and tell the eldersВҰ108684 there what happened. ThenВҰ108671 they should bring \add @the person\add* into the city and give \add вүҲthem a placeВҰ108699 there to live inВҰ108683\add*.
\v 5 \add вүҲNow\add* if a relative of the deceased comes to avengeВҰ108705 the death, \add @the city eldersВҰ108710\add* won'tВҰ108708 handВҰ108714 over the killerВҰ108713 because \add вүҲthe death was accidental andВҰ108703 didn'tВҰ108708 happen because of hate or premeditation\add*.
\v 6 \add вүҲSoВҰ108731 then that person\add* must stay in the city until they're brought before \add вүҲthe panel of judgesВҰ108740\add*. \add If they decide that the death wasn't deliberate,\add* the person must remain in that city until the death of the high priestВҰ108744, then they can \add freely\add* returnВҰ108752 to their own city andВҰ108731 own home.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \add вүҲSoВҰ108769\add* \add @the Israelis\add* chose KedeshВҰ108772 (in the GalileeВҰ108773 region in the hill country of NaftaliВҰ108775) and ShekemВҰ108778 (in the hill country of EfrayimВҰ108780) and KiriatВҰ108783-ArbaВҰ108784 (\add вүҲnow called\add* HebronВҰ108786, in the hill country of YehudahВҰ108788).
\v 8 On the otherВҰ108790 side of the YordanВҰ108791 \add river\add*, theyВҰ108794 chose Betser (in the wildernessВҰ108798 onВҰ108798 the plateauВҰ108799 from the tribe of ReubenВҰ108801), RamotВҰ108804 (in the GileadВҰ108805 from the tribe of GadВҰ108808), andВҰ108790 GolanВҰ108811 (in the BashanВҰ108813 from the tribe of MenashshehВҰ108815).
\v 9 Those were the appointedВҰ108820 citiesВҰ108819 for \add вүҲboth IsraelisВҰ108824 and foreigners living amongВҰ108827\add* them, so that anyoneВҰ108832 who accidentallyВҰ108835 killed someone could flee thereВҰ108829 and \add вүҲbe safe from being avengedВҰ108839 by the deceased's relatives\add* untilВҰ108841 \add вүҲtheyВҰ108818 could receive a proper trial\add*.
\c 21
\s1 The allocation to Levi's descendants
\rem /s1 Towns for the Levites; The Cities of the Levites; Cities Allotted to the Levites; The Towns Given to the Levites
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Then the \add вүҲleaders\add* of the LevitesВҰ108851 went to EleazarВҰ108854 the priestВҰ108855 and to Yehoshua (Nun'sВҰ108861 son) and to the \add вүҲIsraeliВҰ108868 elders\add*\x + \xo 21:2: \xt Num 35:1-8.\x*
\v 2 atВҰ108878 ShilohВҰ108872 (in the CanaanВҰ108874 regionВҰ108873) andВҰ108870 toldВҰ108877 them, вҖңYahwehВҰ108876 saidВҰ108870 \add вүҲthrough\add* MoshehВҰ108880 \add вүҲthat we should be given citiesВҰ108884 to liveВҰ108885 in, along withВҰ108878 theirВҰ108886 surrounding fields\add* for ourВҰ108887 livestockВҰ108887.вҖқ
\v 3 \add вүҲSoВҰ108889 the IsraeliВҰ108892\add* \add leaders\add* gaveВҰ108889 theseВҰ108902 citiesВҰ108901 andВҰ108889 the fields around them to the LevitesВҰ108893 for their inheritanceВҰ108894 \add вүҲas YahwehВҰ108898 had instructed\add*:
\p
\v 4 The first draw wentВҰ108907 to those of the Kohat clansВҰ108909 \add who were\add* descendantsВҰ108912 of AharonВҰ108913 the priestВҰ108914 (from the LevitesВҰ108917). They were allocated thirteen citiesВҰ108925 inВҰ108924 the regions occupied by YehudahВҰ108919, Shimeon, andВҰ108907 BenyaminВҰ108923.
\v 5 The remainingВҰ108932 KohatВҰ108931 \add вүҲclansВҰ108933\add* were \add allocated\add* tenВҰ108945 citiesВҰ108944 inВҰ108943 the regions occupied by EfrayimВҰ108936, DanВҰ108939, and the MenashshehВҰ108942 half-tribe.
\p
\v 6 The Gereshon \add вүҲclansВҰ108950\add* were \add allocated\add* thirteen citiesВҰ108964 in the regions occupied by Yissakar, AsherВҰ108956, NaftaliВҰ108958, and by the MenashshehВҰ108961 half-tribe in the BashanВҰ108962 region.
\p
\v 7 The MerariВҰ108970 clansВҰ108971 were \add allocated\add* twelve citiesВҰ108979 in the regions occupied by ReubenВҰ108973, GadВҰ108976, and ZebulunВҰ108978.
\p
\v 8 \add вүҲSoВҰ108983 the IsraeliВҰ108986 leaders\add* gaveВҰ108983 those citiesВҰ108990 andВҰ108983 theirВҰ108994 surrounding fields to the LevitesВҰ108987, just as YahwehВҰ108997 had instructedВҰ108996 \add вүҲthrough\add* MoshehВҰ109000.
\p
\v 9 These are the names of the citiesВҰ109012 \add вүҲallocated by the Israeli leaders (from the regions occupied by\add* YehudahВҰ109007 and Shimeon)
\v 10 that were given to the Levite Kohat clansВҰ109023 since \add вүҲthey were selected firstВҰ109031 in the draw\add*:
\v 11 KiriatВҰ109037-Arba andВҰ109045 the surroundingВҰ109048 fields (\add вүҲnow called\add* HebronВҰ109042вҖ”Arba was the fatherВҰ109039 of AnakВҰ109040) inВҰ109043 Yehudah'sВҰ109044 hill countryВҰ109043
\v 12 (although the surrounding countryside andВҰ109054 villagesВҰ109056 had already been given to Yefunneh'sВҰ109061 son CalebВҰ109058).
\v 13 \add вүҲSo\add* HebronВҰ109077 was given to the descendantsВҰ109065 of AharonВҰ109067 the priestВҰ109068 and assigned as a refugeВҰ109073 cityВҰ109072 (for anyone who \add accidentally\add* kills someone) along with the surrounding fields, along with LibnahВҰ109083,
\v 14 YattirВҰ109090, EshtemoaВҰ109096,
\v 15 HolonВҰ109103, DebirВҰ109109,
\v 16 AinВҰ109116, Yuttah, and Beyt-ShemeshВҰ109129, all with their surrounding fieldsвҖ”\add a total of\add* nineВҰ109134 citiesВҰ109133 from within Yehudah and Shimeon's \add territories\add*.
\v 17 From Benyamin'sВҰ109142 \add territories\add*, \add the Israeli leaders\add* \add вүҲassigned\add* GibeonВҰ109145, GebaВҰ109151,
\v 18 AnatotВҰ109158, and AlmonВҰ109164вҖ”fourВҰ109169 citiesВҰ109168 and their surrounding fields.
\v 19 \add Thus\add* the descendantsВҰ109174 of AharonВҰ109176 the priestsВҰ109177 \add received\add* thirteen cities with theirВҰ109182 surrounding fields.
\p
\v 20 TheВҰ109192 \add other\add* LeviteВҰ109189 KohatВҰ109188 clansВҰ109185 were allocated citiesВҰ109194 from \add вүҲwithin Efrayim'sВҰ109197 territory\add*:
\v 21 ShekemВҰ109208 (which was assigned as a refugeВҰ109204 cityВҰ109203 for anyone who \add accidentally\add* kills someone), GezerВҰ109216,
\v 22 KibzaimВҰ109223, andВҰ109221 BeytВҰ109229-HoronВҰ109230вҖ”fourВҰ109235 citiesВҰ109234 with their surrounding fields.
\v 23 From Dan'sВҰ109240 \add territory\add*, they were allocated EltekeВҰ109243, GibbetonВҰ109249,
\v 24 AyyalonВҰ109256, and GatВҰ109262-RimmonВҰ109264вҖ”fourВҰ109269 citiesВҰ109268 with their surrounding fields.
\v 25 From the MenashshehВҰ109274 half-tribe's \add territory\add*, they were allocated Taanak and GatВҰ109283-RimmonВҰ109285вҖ”twoВҰ109290 citiesВҰ109289 with their surrounding fields.
\v 26 \add Thus\add* the \add other\add* Levite KohatВҰ109300 clansВҰ109297 \add received\add* tenВҰ109295 citiesВҰ109294 with theirВҰ109296 surrounding fields.
\p
\v 27 The LeviteВҰ109307 Gereshon clansВҰ109306 were allocated cities from \add вүҲwithin the MenashshehВҰ109310 half-tribe's territory\add*: GolanВҰ109318 inВҰ109320 the BashanВҰ109320 (which was assigned as a refugeВҰ109314 city for anyoneВҰ109306 who \add accidentally\add* kills someone) and Be'eshtarahвҖ”two cities withВҰ109320 their surrounding fields.
\v 28 From Yissakar's \add territory\add*, they were allocated Kishyon, DaberatВҰ109344,
\v 29 Yarmut, and Eyn-GannimВҰ109358вҖ”fourВҰ109363 citiesВҰ109362 with their surrounding fields.
\v 30 From Asher'sВҰ109367 \add territory\add*, they were allocated MishalВҰ109370, AbdonВҰ109376,
\v 31 HelkatВҰ109383, and RehobВҰ109389вҖ”fourВҰ109394 citiesВҰ109393 with their surrounding fields.
\v 32 From Naftali'sВҰ109398 \add territory\add*, they were allocated KedeshВҰ109407 inВҰ109408 the GalileeВҰ109408 (which was assigned as a refugeВҰ109403 cityВҰ109401 for anyone who \add accidentally\add* kills someone), HammotВҰ109414-DorВҰ109415, and KartanВҰ109421вҖ”threeВҰ109426 citiesВҰ109425 withВҰ109408 their surrounding fields.
\v 33 \add Thus\add* the Levite Gereshon clan \add received\add* thirteen citiesВҰ109430 with their surrounding fields.
\p
\v 34 The remainingВҰ109445 LeviteВҰ109444 MerariВҰ109443 clansВҰ109440 were allocated cities from \add вүҲwithin Zebulun'sВҰ109448 territory\add*: YokneamВҰ109451, KartahВҰ109457,
\v 35 DimnahВҰ109464, and NahalalВҰ109470вҖ”fourВҰ109475 citiesВҰ109474 with their surrounding fields.
\v 36 From Reuben'sВҰ109478 \add territory\add*, they were allocated BezerВҰ109481, YahazВҰ109487,
\v 37 KedemotВҰ109494, and MephaatВҰ109500вҖ”fourВҰ109505 citiesВҰ109504 with their surrounding fields.
\v 38 From Gad'sВҰ109510 \add territory\add*, they were allocated RamotВҰ109518 inВҰ109519 the GileadВҰ109519 (which was assigned as a refugeВҰ109514 cityВҰ109513 for anyone who \add accidentally\add* kills someone), MahanaimВҰ109525,
\v 39 HeshbonВҰ109532, and YazerВҰ109538вҖ”fourВҰ109545 citiesВҰ109544 with their surrounding fields.
\v 40 \add Thus\add* the LeviteВҰ109555 MerariВҰ109551 clan \add received\add* twelve cities in the draw, along with their surrounding fields.
\p
\v 41 \add SoВҰ109569\add* altogether the LevitesВҰ109564 received forty-eight cities and theirВҰ109573 surrounding fields from with the territories of the \add вүҲother tribes\add*вҖ”
\v 42 each of those cities had fields aroundВҰ109581 them \add for their livestock to graze on\add*.
\s1 The Israelis move into the regions
\rem /s1 Israel Takes Possession of the Land
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 43 \add вүҲThus\add* YahwehВҰ109590 gaveВҰ109589 \add вүҲthe Israelis\add* all the land thatВҰ109597 he'd promisedВҰ109598 theirВҰ109600 ancestorsВҰ109600 would be given and \add so the people\add* \add вүҲmoved into those regions\add* and livedВҰ109602 there.
\v 44 Yahweh gave them \add вүҲpeace\add* as he'd promisedВҰ109612 their ancestorsВҰ109613вҖ”none of their enemies could standВҰ109616 against them \add вүҲbecause Yahweh helped them defeat any enemies\add*.
\v 45 \add вүҲYahwehВҰ109640 kept everyВҰ109645 promiseВҰ109635 thatВҰ109637 he'd made to the IsraelisВҰ109644вҖ”it all happened just like he'd said\add*.
\c 22
\s1 The eastern tribes return home
\rem /s1 The Eastern Tribes Return to Their Territory; Eastern Tribes Return Home; Joshua Sends the Eastern Tribes Home; The Eastern Tribes Return Home
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Then Yehoshua \add вүҲsummonedВҰ109650\add* the tribesВҰ109655 of Reuben and Gad, and the MenashshehВҰ109656 half-tribe
\v 2 andВҰ109671 told them, вҖңYou yourselves have obeyedВҰ109671 everything that Yahweh's servantВҰ109669 MoshehВҰ109668 instructedВҰ109666 you to do. In addition, you've all followed everything that I told you.\x + \xo 22:2: \xt Num 32:20-32; Josh 1:12-15.\x*
\v 3 You've all \add ^supported\add* your \add вүҲfellow tribes\add* all this timeВҰ109686 and fulfilled what your godВҰ109697 YahwehВҰ109696 \add вүҲrequested of youВҰ109681 all\add*,
\v 4 andВҰ109699 now \add *he\add* has enabled \add вүҲthese other tribes\add* to rest \add from battle\add* just like he told them he would. \add вүҲSoВҰ109699\add* now, you all may goВҰ109709 back to your homes thatВҰ109716 Yahweh's servantВҰ109721 MoshehВҰ109720 gaveВҰ109718 you onВҰ109723 the \add вүҲother\add* side of the river.
\v 5 Only do takeВҰ109728 care to \add continue to\add* obey the instructions and the law thatВҰ109737 Yahweh's servantВҰ109741 MoshehВҰ109740 gave you: to loveВҰ109744 your godВҰ109748 Yahweh, to \add вүҲfollow him and his instructions\add*, to \add вүҲstay close to him\add*, and to serveВҰ109758 him with all your heartsВҰ109761 and your \add inner\add* selves.вҖқ
\v 6 ThenВҰ109766 YehoshuaВҰ109767 blessedВҰ109766 them andВҰ109766 sentВҰ109768 them on their way to return to their \add вүҲhomes\add*.
\v 7 (MoshehВҰ109780 had given the BashanВҰ109781 to the half of the MenashshehВҰ109778 half-tribe, and Yehoshua had given \add land\add* onВҰ109781 the \add вүҲwestern\add* side of the YordanВҰ109791 to the otherВҰ109788 half.) \add When\add* he'd blessedВҰ109800 them
\v 8 he'd saidВҰ109802, вҖңGo back to your \add вүҲhomes\add* with many richesВҰ109805: plenty of livestockВҰ109811, and with silverВҰ109815, goldВҰ109816, bronzeВҰ109817, and iron, and with lots of clothingВҰ109819. Share the plunder from your enemiesВҰ109825 with \add вүҲthose who remained behind\add*.вҖқ
\v 9 So \add вүҲthe warriors from the tribesВҰ109841 of\add* Reuven, GadВҰ109838, and the MenashshehВҰ109842 half-tribe left the \add вүҲothers\add* there atВҰ109863 ShilohВҰ109846 in the CanaanВҰ109850 regionВҰ109848, and wentВҰ109832 back to theirВҰ109859 ownВҰ109859 land in GileadВҰ109855 \add across the river\add* which theyВҰ109861 had taken for themselves withВҰ109863 the agreement of YahwehВҰ109867 given through MoshehВҰ109870.
\s1 The altar by the Yordan
\rem /s1 A Memorial Altar East of the Jordan; The Altar by the Jordan; The Eastern Tribes Build a Memorial
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 10 \add вүҲThe warriors from the tribesВҰ109888 of\add* Reuven, GadВҰ109886, and the MenashshehВҰ109889 half-tribe arrived at the YordanВҰ109894 river (still on the CanaanВҰ109879 side) and theyВҰ109872 builtВҰ109880 a very largeВҰ109896 and noticeable altar thereВҰ109890 \add before crossing over to go home\add*.
\v 11 \add WhenВҰ109899\add* the \add other\add* \add вүҲIsraelisВҰ109902\add* heardВҰ109899 \add about it\add*, theyВҰ109905 said, вҖңLook, the men \add вүҲfrom the tribesВҰ109913 of\add* Reuven, GadВҰ109911, andВҰ109899 the MenashshehВҰ109914 half-tribe have builtВҰ109905 the altarВҰ109917 at the \add вүҲentrance to this\add* CanaanВҰ109922 regionВҰ109921 down at the YordanВҰ109926 on \add *our\add* side.вҖқ
\p
\v 12 \add вүҲHearing that, those from the western side of the Yordan assembledВҰ109936 at ShilohВҰ109943 to goВҰ109944 to battleВҰ109946 with the two andВҰ109936 a half tribes on the eastern side\add*.
\v 13 \add Meanwhile\add*, theyВҰ109949 sentВҰ109949 the priestВҰ109979 Finehas (Eleazar'sВҰ109978 son) \add across\add* into the GileadВҰ109972 regionВҰ109971 \add to talk\add* with \add the leaders from\add* the tribesВҰ109966 of ReubenВҰ109957, GadВҰ109962, and the MenashshehВҰ109968 half-tribe.
\v 14 \add @Finehas\add* took ten leaders with himвҖ”important leaders from each of the IsraeliВҰ109991 tribesВҰ109991 \add from the western side\add*.
\v 15 They \add crossed over\add* to the GileadВҰ110022 regionВҰ110021 to talk to \add the leaders from\add* the tribesВҰ110016 of ReubenВҰ110007, GadВҰ110012, andВҰ110002 the MenashshehВҰ110018 half-tribe. They saidВҰ110023,
\v 16 вҖңYahweh's people are \add вүҲasking\add*, вҖҳWhat's this unfaithfulness thatВҰ110037 you all have done unfaithfully against Yisrael'sВҰ110040 godВҰ110039вҖ”turningВҰ110041 away from Yahweh when you builtВҰ110045 an altarВҰ110047 for yourselvesВҰ110045 today inВҰ110039 rebellionВҰ110048 against Yahweh?\x + \xo 22:16: \xt Deu 12:13-14.\x*
\v 17 Wasn't \add вүҲour disobedience atВҰ110069 PeorВҰ110058\add*\x + \xo 22:17: \xt Num 25:1-9.\x* \add вүҲbad enoughВҰ110052 for you\add*? We haven't \add вүҲgotten over it\add* to this dayВҰ110065. Plus there was a plagueВҰ110068 amongВҰ110069 Yahweh's people.
\v 18 ButВҰ110072 all of youвҖ”are you turningВҰ110073 away from Yahweh today? If you all rebelВҰ110079 againstВҰ110083 Yahweh today, tomorrowВҰ110082 he'll be furious atВҰ110081 all of us.
\v 19 ButВҰ110091 if it's because you all think this land here is defiled, thenВҰ110091 crossВҰ110097 back over to Yahweh's ownВҰ110096 land whereВҰ110104 he lives inВҰ110111 his sacredВҰ110108 tentВҰ110108. \add вүҲEither way\add* don'tВҰ110113 rebel againstВҰ110112 Yahweh by buildingВҰ110120 \add this otherВҰ110123\add* altar for yourselves that's distinct from ourВҰ110111 godВҰ110126 Yahweh's altar.
\v 20 Didn't Akan act unfaithfullyВҰ110134 \add вүҲtaking something that was forbidden\add*\x + \xo 22:20: \xt Josh 7:1-26.\x* and \add вүҲall of us suffered as a result of itВҰ110143\add*? \add вүҲIt wasn't just him alone that died because of that\add*.вҖҷ вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \add TheВҰ110168 leaders from\add* the tribesВҰ110161 of ReubenВҰ110156, GadВҰ110159, and the MenashshehВҰ110162 half-tribe answeredВҰ110153 \add вүҲthe other leaders\add*,
\v 22 вҖңYahweh is the god of gods. Yahweh is the god of gods. He knows, and as for \add вүҲthe Israeli people\add*, let \add #them\add* knowВҰ110184 \add also\add*вҖ”if it was in rebellionВҰ110187 or in unfaithfulnessВҰ110190 against Yahweh, don'tВҰ110192 \add вүҲbother trying to save us today\add*.
\v 23 If \add вүҲwe'd aimed\add* to buildВҰ110198 an altarВҰ110200 for ourselves to turnВҰ110201 \add away\add* from followingВҰ110202 Yahweh, or if it was to offer burntВҰ110208 offerings or grainВҰ110209 offerings on it, or if to make the sacrificesВҰ110214 of peaceВҰ110215 offerings on it, Yahweh himself will \add вүҲhandle it\add*.
\v 24 \add вүҲButВҰ110220 no, we did it becauseВҰ110224 we foresaw a potential problem: what if in the future, your descendants ask our descendants\add* \add over here on this side of the river\add*, вҖҳWhat \add вүҲdo youВҰ110237 lot have to do with\add* Yisrael'sВҰ110240 godВҰ110239 YahwehВҰ110238?
\v 25 \add вүҲYahweh has given this YordanВҰ110256 river as a borderВҰ110242 between us, and you descendants of ReubenВҰ110250 and GadВҰ110253\add*. \add вүҲYou all don'tВҰ110257 have any part\add* inВҰ110261 Yahweh.вҖҷ ThenВҰ110242 your descendants might make ourВҰ110266 descendants \add вүҲstop worshipping\add* Yahweh.
\v 26 \add вүҲSoВҰ110279 weВҰ110273 decided\add* to buildВҰ110278 the altarВҰ110281вҖ”not to be used for burntВҰ110283 offeringsВҰ110283 or for sacrificesВҰ110285,
\v 27 butВҰ110291 as a \add вүҲsymbol to remind\add* our future descendants and yours, that \add вүҲwe all truly worship Yahweh\add* withВҰ110301 our burntВҰ110301 offerings, our sacrificesВҰ110302, and our peaceВҰ110303 offerings, so yourВҰ110307 descendants can'tВҰ110304 tell our future descendants that \add вүҲwe have no business worshipping\add* Yahweh.
\v 28 \add вүҲIf they do say anything like that, thenВҰ110316 our descendantsВҰ110324 will be able to reply\add*, вҖҳSee that copy of Yahweh's altarВҰ110331 whichВҰ110333 isn'tВҰ110337 used for burntВҰ110338 offeringsВҰ110338 or sacrificesВҰ110340, our ancestorsВҰ110336 built that as a reminder for both you all andВҰ110316 us.вҖҷ
\v 29 May any idea of rebellingВҰ110351 againstВҰ110352 Yahweh stay far from us. \add вүҲSame withВҰ110352 any idea of\add* buildingВҰ110357 any altar apart from ourВҰ110365 godВҰ110365 Yahweh's \add genuine\add* altar for burntВҰ110359 offerings, or grainВҰ110360 offerings, or otherВҰ110362 sacrificesВҰ110361.вҖқ
\p
\v 30 \add вүҲSo\add* Finehas the priestВҰ110373 and the other community and clan leadersВҰ110374 withВҰ110395 him, listenedВҰ110371 to what the descendantsВҰ110386 of Reuven, GadВҰ110391, and MenashshehВҰ110393 told them, and it \add вүҲsounded sensible to them\add*,
\v 31 \add вүҲso\add* Finehas (\add the late\add* Eleazar'sВҰ110401 son) told \add *them\add*, вҖңToday weВҰ110419 realise that Yahweh is amongВҰ110422 us andВҰ110397 that you all haven't actedВҰ110427 unfaithfullyВҰ110427 againstВҰ110428 \add *him\add*, so therefore you've prevented Yahweh \add вүҲfrom needing to punish us\add*.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 ThenВҰ110440 Finehas and the other leadersВҰ110447 left GileadВҰ110457 and returnedВҰ110440 back \add across the Yordan\add* to the CanaanВҰ110461 regionВҰ110456 where \add вүҲmost of the IsraelisВҰ110465 resided\add*, taking back a \add good\add* report.
\v 33 \add вүҲThe people were pleased with thatВҰ110488 newsВҰ110471\add*, and they \add вүҲthanked\add* GodВҰ110476 and stopped talking about goingВҰ110481 to war with Reuven and GadВҰ110494 \add across the river\add* and destroyingВҰ110484 \add *them\add*.
\p
\v 34 The descendantsВҰ110499 of Reuven andВҰ110502 GadВҰ110504 named the altarВҰ110505 \add вҖҳReminderвҖҷ\add* because itВҰ110508 was a reminder betweenВҰ110509 them that YahwehВҰ110511 is GodВҰ110512.
\c 23
\s1 Yehoshua's final speech
\rem /s1 Joshua's Farewell to the Leaders; Joshua Exhorts the People; Joshua's farewell and death; Joshua's Final Words to Israel; Joshua's Farewell Address
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 \add вүҲA long timeВҰ110516 passed\add* and YahwehВҰ110522 had givenВҰ110521 YisraelВҰ110523 \add вүҲpeace without attacks\add* from theirВҰ110526 enemiesВҰ110526 all around, and Yehoshua was \add now\add* \add вүҲin his old age\add*,
\v 2 \add вүҲso\add* he summoned all the Israeli eldersВҰ110538 and leaders, along with the judgesВҰ110540 and officialsВҰ110541. He told them, вҖңNow I'm in my old age,
\v 3 \add вүҲbutВҰ110549\add* you all have seenВҰ110550 what YahwehВҰ110556 did to all those \add вүҲkingdomsВҰ110560\add* ahead of you, becauseВҰ110562 \add *he's\add* the one who fightsВҰ110567 for you all.
\v 4 I'veВҰ110571 allocated the remainingВҰ110576 \add вүҲkingdomsВҰ110575\add* that youВҰ110572 all will defeat as an inheritanceВҰ110578 for yourВҰ110579 tribesВҰ110579, alongside those that I conquered from the YordanВҰ110582 to the Mediterranean inВҰ110578 the west
\v 5 YourВҰ110597 godВҰ110594 YahwehВҰ110607 will push them out ahead of you all andВҰ110593 capture theirВҰ110604 lands for you to possessВҰ110601, just as \add *he\add* told you he would.
\v 6 TakeВҰ110615 great care to obey andВҰ110611 do everythingВҰ110616 that MoshehВҰ110621 wroteВҰ110618 downвҖ”don'tВҰ110622 deviate from it inВҰ110619 any way.
\v 7 Don't enter those remainingВҰ110634 \add вүҲkingdomsВҰ110632\add*, and don't mention the nameВҰ110637 of their godsВҰ110638 or make an oath using their namesВҰ110637 and don't worship or bow down to them.
\v 8 Instead you all should clingВҰ110655 to your godВҰ110654 YahwehВҰ110653, just as you've done untilВҰ110658 now.
\v 9 \add Yes,\add* YahwehВҰ110663 has drivenВҰ110662 away many greatВҰ110666 kingdomsВҰ110665 ahead of you all, andВҰ110662 untilВҰ110674 this dayВҰ110675, none of them have stood against you.
\v 10 Just one of you \add вүҲcan make a thousandВҰ110684 men flee\add*, because YahwehВҰ110687 is yourВҰ110681 godВҰ110688вҖ”he's the one who fightsВҰ110690 for you just \add вүҲlike he said he would\add*.\x + \xo 23:10: a \xt Deu 32:30; \xo b \xt Deu 3:22.\x*
\v 11 \add вүҲMakeВҰ110700 a great effort to guard yourselves\add* that you all \add continue\add* to loveВҰ110699 your godВҰ110703 YahwehВҰ110702.
\v 12 \add Yes,\add* if you all ever turn away \add from him\add* and instead clingВҰ110711 to those remaining kingdomsВҰ110713 or remaining people, and if you intermarryВҰ110718 with them or associateВҰ110720 with them,
\v 13 you all will certainly \add soon\add* find out that your god Yahweh will not continue to driveВҰ110732 out theseВҰ110736 nationsВҰ110735 \add вүҲahead of you\add*. Then they will \add end up\add* trapping and snaring you all, and be like a whip on your sidesВҰ110743 and like thornsВҰ110744 inВҰ110743 your eyesВҰ110745, untilВҰ110746 you all perishВҰ110748 from on this goodВҰ110751 land that Yahweh your god has givenВҰ110754 you.
\p
\v 14 Listen, today I'm about to go the wayВҰ110763 \add вүҲthat everyoneВҰ110779 has to go\add* and you all know with all your heartВҰ110770 and with all your soul that not one thing has \add вүҲfailed to comeВҰ110790 true\add* from all the good thingsВҰ110782 that your godВҰ110787 YahwehВҰ110786 said about you. \add вүҲEverything has happened as saidвҖ”down to the very last word\add*.
\v 15 And \add вүҲjust like all those good things came true\add*, so \add too\add* YahwehВҰ110810 will \add вүҲsend all the punishments he promised you all\add* \add if you disobey him\add*, \add вүҲeven if it means that\add* he destroysВҰ110824 you all from this good land that \add *he's\add* givenВҰ110831 you.
\v 16 IfВҰ110854 you ignore the agreement withВҰ110855 your godВҰ110841 YahwehВҰ110840 and \add disobey\add* his commandsВҰ110843 and goВҰ110845 and serveВҰ110846 otherВҰ110848 godsВҰ110847 and bow down to them, then \add *his\add* \add вүҲangerВҰ110852 will flare up\add* against you all and you'll quicklyВҰ110857 \add вүҲbe wiped out\add* from the goodВҰ110860 land thatВҰ110842 he has givenВҰ110862 you.вҖқ
\c 24
\s1 The promise again of Yisrael's descendants
\rem /s1 The Covenant Renewed at Shechem; The Lord's Covenant Renewed; Joshua Speaks to the People at Shechem; The Tribes Renew the Covenant
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 1 Then Yehoshua assembled all the tribesВҰ110872 of YisraelВҰ110873 at ShekemВҰ110874. He summoned their eldersВҰ110876, leaders, judgesВҰ110879, and officersВҰ110880, and theyВҰ110881 presentedВҰ110881 themselvesВҰ110881 before GodВҰ110883,
\v 2 and Yehoshua told all the peopleВҰ110891, вҖңYahwehВҰ110895, the godВҰ110896 of YisraelВҰ110897 says: Your ancestorsВҰ110901 \add includingВҰ110906\add* TerahВҰ110903 the father of AbrahamВҰ110905 and NahorВҰ110907, lived beyondВҰ110898 the \add Euphrates\add* riverВҰ110899 from long ago, \add вүҲbutВҰ110885\add* they \add вүҲworshipped\add* otherВҰ110910 gods.\x + \xo 24:2: \xt Gen 11:27.\x*
\v 3 ThenВҰ110912 I tookВҰ110912 your ancestorВҰ110915 AbrahamВҰ110918 from beyondВҰ110919 the riverВҰ110920 and brought him \add вүҲacross\add* all the land of CanaanВҰ110926, and I multipliedВҰ110927 his \add вүҲdescendants\add*, \add вүҲincludingВҰ110921\add* giving him IsaacВҰ110937.\x + \xo 24:3: a \xt Gen 12:1-9; \xo b \xt Gen 21:1-3.\x*
\v 4 ThenВҰ110939 I gave Yacob and Esau to IsaacВҰ110940, and I gave Esau the hillВҰ110951 country of SeirВҰ110952 \add вүҲbutВҰ110939\add* Yacob and his sonsВҰ110956 went down to EgyptВҰ110958.\x + \xo 24:4: a \xt Gen 25:24-26; \xo b \xt Gen 36:8; Deu 2:5; \xo c \xt Gen 46:1-7.\x*
\v 5 I sentВҰ110960 MoshehВҰ110963 and AharonВҰ110966 and I damaged EgyptВҰ110970 internally, and thenВҰ110960 I broughtВҰ110975 youВҰ110976 all out \add again\add*.\x + \xo 24:5: \xt Exo 3:1вҖ“12:42.\x*
\v 6 I broughtВҰ110978 your ancestorsВҰ110981 out of EgyptВҰ110982, and you all cameВҰ110983 to the \add edge\add* of the Red Sea. \add вүҲThe Egyptians\add* chased afterВҰ110987 \add *them\add* withВҰ110989 chariotsВҰ110989 and horsemenВҰ110990\x + \xo 24:6-7: \xt Exo 14:1-31.\x*
\v 7 and \add @the people\add* criedВҰ110995 out to YahwehВҰ110998, and he placed darknessВҰ111000 between you and the Egyptians. \add After bringing you all through the sea,\add* he broughtВҰ111005 the sea over \add вүҲthe Egyptian army and drowned them\add*. Your \add own\add* eyesВҰ111012 saw what I did to EgyptВҰ111017. ThenВҰ110995 you all livedВҰ111018 a long timeВҰ111020 inВҰ111017 the wildernessВҰ111019.
\p
\v 8 вҖң\add After that,\add* I broughtВҰ111023 you to the regionВҰ111028 of the AmoritesВҰ111029 who livedВҰ111030 onВҰ111031 the \add вүҲeastern\add* side of the YordanВҰ111032, and theyВҰ111033 battled against you all, \add вүҲbutВҰ111023 I gaveВҰ111035 you victory over them\add* and I destroyedВҰ111042 them from \add вүҲahead of you\add* and you all tookВҰ111038 over theirВҰ111041 land.\x + \xo 24:8: \xt Num 21:21-35.\x*
\v 9 ThenВҰ111045 (Zippor'sВҰ111049 son) KingВҰ111053 BalakВҰ111046 of MoabВҰ111051 \add вүҲprepared his warriors\add* and foughtВҰ111052 againstВҰ111053 \add *you all\add* and he \add вүҲsummoned\add* (Beor'sВҰ111059 son) BalaamВҰ111056 to curseВҰ111060 you.\x + \xo 24:9-10: \xt Num 22:1вҖ“24:25.\x*
\v 10 \add вүҲButВҰ111063\add* I wasn't willingВҰ111064 to listenВҰ111065 to BalaamВҰ111066, \add вүҲso instead,\add* he blessedВҰ111067 you all repeatedly andВҰ111063 I rescuedВҰ111070 you from \add вүҲKing Balak\add*.
\v 11 ThenВҰ111074 you crossedВҰ111074 over the YordanВҰ111077 \add river\add* and \add вүҲarrived atВҰ111083\add* Yericho. The men of Yericho foughtВҰ111082 againstВҰ111083 you all, \add as did\add* the AmoritesВҰ111087, the PerizzitesВҰ111088, the CanaanitesВҰ111089, the HittitesВҰ111090, the GirgashitesВҰ111091, the HivitesВҰ111092, and the Yebusites \add вүҲbutВҰ111074 I helped you all to defeat them\add*.\x + \xo 24:11: a \xt Josh 3:14-17; \xo b \xt Josh 6:1-21.\x*
\v 12 I sentВҰ111098 hornetsВҰ111102\f + \fr 24:12 \ft The Hebrew word вҖҳЧҰЦҙЧЁЦ°ЧўЦёЧ”вҖҷ (вҖҳhornetвҖҷ, but pluralised here in the OET-RV) may have some non-literal meaning here, e.g., вҖҳpanicвҖҷ, or it may be a general reference to any manifestation of God's anger.\f* \add вүҲaheadВҰ111099 of you all\add* andВҰ111098 they droveВҰ111103 out the twoВҰ111106 AmoriteВҰ111108 kingsВҰ111107вҖ”it wasn't yourВҰ111099 swordsВҰ111110 or bows that did it.\x + \xo 24:12: \xt Exo 23:28; Deu 7:20.\x*
\v 13 \add вүҲSoВҰ111114\add* I gaveВҰ111114 you all a land which you didn't \add вүҲearn yourselves\add* and citiesВҰ111123 to live inВҰ111122 that you all didn't build yourselves. You all are \add вүҲbenefitting from\add* vineyardsВҰ111130 and oliveВҰ111131 grovesВҰ111131 that you didn't plantВҰ111135.вҖқ\x + \xo 24:13: \xt Deu 6:10-11.\x*
\p
\v 14 \add The Yehoshua continued,\add* вҖңNow you all must \add вүҲrespect\add* Yahweh and faithfullyВҰ111147 serve him withВҰ111146 \add вүҲyour complete beings\add*. And you all must removeВҰ111148 the \add вүҲidols\add* thatВҰ111152 your ancestorsВҰ111154 servedВҰ111153 beyondВҰ111155 the \add вүҲEuphrates\add* and inВҰ111146 EgyptВҰ111157, and \add only\add* serve Yahweh.
\v 15 But if \add вүҲyou all dislike\add* serving Yahweh, thenВҰ111163 chooseВҰ111170 for yourselves today who you will serve: perhaps the gods yourВҰ111165 fathersВҰ111184 \add once\add* served beyondВҰ111186 the \add вүҲEuphrates\add*, or the gods of the AmoriteВҰ111194 \add people\add* inВҰ111165 whoseВҰ111198 land you are \add now\add* livingВҰ111197. But as for me andВҰ111163 my householdВҰ111200, we will serve Yahweh.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖң\add вүҲWe'dВҰ111213 never even consider\add* leaving YahwehВҰ111215 to serveВҰ111216 otherВҰ111218 godsВҰ111217,вҖқ the peopleВҰ111208 respondedВҰ111209,
\v 17 вҖңbecause YahwehВҰ111221 is our godВҰ111222. He is the one who broughtВҰ111224 us and our ancestorsВҰ111228 out from slaveryВҰ111232 in the land of EgyptВҰ111230, and who did those greatВҰ111239 miracles \add вүҲright in front of\add* our eyesВҰ111235. Also, he looked after us \add вүҲonВҰ111247 our entireВҰ111242 journey\add* and amongВҰ111248 all the peopleВҰ111249 groups thatВҰ111233 we passedВҰ111251 by.
\v 18 Yahweh droveВҰ111254 all the peoplesВҰ111260 out \add вүҲahead of us\add*, even the AmoritesВҰ111263 who lived in that region. \add SoВҰ111254\add* we too we will serveВҰ111270 Yahweh because he is ourВҰ111266 godВҰ111277.вҖқ
\p
\v 19 вҖңYou all won't be able to serveВҰ111287 YahwehВҰ111290,вҖқ \add вүҲwarned\add* Yehoshua, вҖңbecause he's a god \add вүҲwho cannot mix with sin\add*. He's a jealousВҰ111298 GodВҰ111293вҖ”he won't \add вүҲforgiveВҰ111302 your rebellion and disobedience\add*.
\v 20 If you abandonВҰ111307 YahwehВҰ111310 and serveВҰ111311 the godsВҰ111312 of \add вүҲother nations\add*, then he'll turnВҰ111314 and do harm to you all and destroy you, \add вүҲeven if he's previously been\add* goodВҰ111322 to you all.вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \add вүҲButВҰ111325\add* the peopleВҰ111326 \add вүҲanswered\add* Yehoshua, вҖңNo, weВҰ111335 will worship YahwehВҰ111334.вҖқ
\v 22 ThenВҰ111337 Yehoshua \add вүҲcautioned\add* the peopleВҰ111341, вҖңYou all are witnesses against yourselves, that you yourselves have chosenВҰ111348 to serveВҰ111353 YahwehВҰ111352.вҖқ
\p вҖң\add We are\add* witnesses,вҖқ theyВҰ111355 \add вүҲconfirmed\add*.
\p
\v 23 вҖңThenВҰ111358 \add you all go right\add* now and removeВҰ111359 the foreignВҰ111363 godsВҰ111362 thatВҰ111364 you already have, and turn yourВҰ111365 heartsВҰ111369 towards YahwehВҰ111372, the godВҰ111373 of YisraelВҰ111374,вҖқ \add said Yehoshua\add*.
\p
\v 24 вҖңWeВҰ111380 will serveВҰ111385 our godВҰ111384 YahwehВҰ111383, andВҰ111376 we will listenВҰ111387 to hisВҰ111386 voiceВҰ111386,вҖқ the peopleВҰ111377 \add вүҲreplied\add*.
\p
\v 25 \add вүҲSoВҰ111389\add* YehoshuaВҰ111390 \add вүҲmade a formal agreement\add* withВҰ111399 the peopleВҰ111392 inВҰ111399 ShekemВҰ111399 onВҰ111399 that dayВҰ111393, \add вүҲestablishing rules andВҰ111389 laws\add* for them.
\v 26 \add *He\add* wroteВҰ111401 \add *them\add* inВҰ111407 the book of God's law. ThenВҰ111401 he tookВҰ111410 a largeВҰ111412 stoneВҰ111411 andВҰ111401 set it up thereВҰ111414 beneath the oak tree thatВҰ111417 was \add вүҲby Yahweh's sacredВҰ111418 tentВҰ111418\add*.
\v 27 вҖңLook atВҰ111434 this stoneВҰ111430,вҖқ Yehoshua saidВҰ111422 to all the peopleВҰ111428. вҖңIt will be for a witness against us, because it has heardВҰ111439 \add вүҲeverything thatВҰ111445 YahwehВҰ111444 has instructed\add* us, and it will be for a witness against you all, inВҰ111434 case you act deceptively against your godВҰ111454.вҖқ
\rem /s1 Buried in the Promised Land
\v 28 ThenВҰ111456 YehoshuaВҰ111457 sentВҰ111456 \add all\add* the peopleВҰ111460 off to go to theirВҰ111462 allotted regions.
\s1 The deaths of Yehoshua and Eleazar
\rem /s1 Leaders Buried in the Promised Land; Death of Joshua and Eleazar; Joshua and Eleazar Die
\s4 Promised land
\p
\v 29 After all that, Nun'sВҰ111473 son and Yahweh's servantВҰ111474 Yehoshua diedВҰ111469 at the age of 110.
\v 30 They buriedВҰ111482 him in his alloted property atВҰ111484 TimnatВҰ111486-Serah whichВҰ111489 is in the EfrayimВҰ111492 hillВҰ111494 countryВҰ111490 northВҰ111493 of MtВҰ111494. Ga'ash.\x + \xo 24:30: \xt Josh 19:49-50.\x*
\p
\v 31 The \add вүҲIsraelis\add* had servedВҰ111498 Yahweh all through Yehoshua's lifetime and throughout the lifetimes of the eldersВҰ111509 who lived longer than Yehoshua and who had experienced everything thatВҰ111515 Yahweh had done for YisraelВҰ111499.
\p
\v 32 They buriedВҰ111538 Yosef's bonesВҰ111528 (that they had carried out from EgyptВҰ111537) in ShekemвҖ”in the portionВҰ111540 of the fieldВҰ111541 that YacobВҰ111544 had boughtВҰ111543 from the sonsВҰ111546 of HamorВҰ111548 (Shekem's fatherВҰ111549) for a hundredВҰ111552 coins, andВҰ111526 \add @that land\add* became the inheritanceВҰ111558 of Yosef's descendantsВҰ111555.\x + \xo 24:32: \xt Gen 33:19; 50:24-25; Exo 13:19; Yhn 4:5; Acts 7:16.\x*
\p
\v 33 Aharon's son Eleazar \add also\add* diedВҰ111564 andВҰ111565 was buriedВҰ111565 atВҰ111567 GibeahВҰ111567вҖ”the city thatВҰ111570 belonged to his son Finehas inВҰ111567 the EfrayimВҰ111575 hill countryВҰ111574.
